<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="70%">
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+2>&quot;SAS70&quot;<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=+0>The audit that checks to see if the manager is doing
what they tell you they are doing.</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<BR>

<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></H3>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+1>What does this mean to you?</FONT></FONT></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">Money managers are more inclined to voluntarily
submit to self examination when requested by a client or a potential client.
If your a pension fund trustee, you are in the position of influence regarding
norms of practice within the industry. The funds &quot;drive&quot; the
marketplace. As an example, when the money management industry adopted
standards for presentation of performance results (AIMR Standards), many
carried the cause to their staff and to their boards. As a result, AIMR
is the standard of standards today. We believe SAS 70 audits are next.</FONT></P>

<CENTER><P>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Ashland
Accounting Services, P.C.<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="mailto:info@aascpa.com">info@aascpa.com</A></FONT></FONT></P></CENTER>
</TD>
