<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="70%">
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+2>&quot;SAS70&quot;<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=+0>The audit that checks to see if the manager is doing
what they tell you they are doing.</FONT></FONT></B><BR>
<BR>

<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></H3>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+1>Investment Advisor SAS 70<BR>
Control Objectives</FONT></FONT></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">Procedures are in place to ensure trades are valid,
complete and recorded timely:</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(1) Investment transactions are executed by authorized
personnel with authorized counterparties, in accordance with established
investment strategies.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(2) Investment transactions are appropriately
allocated to customer accounts under established allocation methodologies.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(3) Third Party confirmations/affirmations are
obtained for each transaction.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(4) Investment transactions are communicated timely
to the appropriate Custodian, Trustee and Record keeper.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(5) Portfolio cash, positions, and value balances
are regularly reconciled with the appropriate Custodian, Trustee and Record
keeper and reconciling items are resolved, documented and filed in a timely
manner. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(6) All investment and cash transaction data is
captured and recorded on trade date. </FONT></P>

<CENTER><P>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Ashland
Accounting Services, P.C.<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="mailto:info@aascpa.com">info@aascpa.com</A></FONT></FONT></P></CENTER>
</TD>
