<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+2>&quot;SAS70&quot;<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=+0>The audit that checks to see if the manager is doing
what they tell you they are doing.</FONT></FONT></B><BR>

<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></H3>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+1>Procedures are in place
to ensure accurate client reporting:</FONT></FONT></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(1) Positions are properly valued, using prices
obtained independent of the portfolio manager function.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(2) Income and corporate actions are properly
accrued.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(3) Performance information provided to customers
on statements is properly calculated in accordance with established criteria.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(4) Accounts are properly billed based on the
provisions in the advisory agreements.</FONT></P>

<CENTER><P>
