<TD WIDTH="10%"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="70%">
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+2>&quot;WWW&quot;<BR>
</FONT>Web sites for finance professionals by finance professionals</FONT></B></H3>

<CENTER><P>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C">The World Wide Web</FONT></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">No one can predict the consequences of the Internet
connecting millions of individuals with one another and to billions of
pieces of information in an unstructured, constantly evolving environment.
One thing is certain, though, commerce and advertising will be changing
at an ever quickening pace.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">The great commercial value of the Internet is
that Net users &quot;pull&quot; information of value to themselves vs.
having it &quot;pushed&quot; upon them. In our time-starved era, instant
on-demand information is the lubricant for commerce.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">The ability for investment firms to interact with
potential and existing customers via the Internet will create marketing
opportunities that will transform the way we do business.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">On balance, we think the promises of the Internet
outweigh the threats. For the investment management community, the Internet
seems to be the most likely step in preparing for the future. Having a
presence on the Internet will become essential as business takes an increasingly
global oreintation.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">Over-hyped? Maybe or maybe not. Necessary? We
think so. A smart place to be? Definitely.&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<CENTER><P>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Ashland
Accounting Services, P.C.<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="mailto:info@aascpa.com">info@aascpa.com</A></FONT></FONT></P></CENTER>
