<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#000040" LINK="#408080" VLINK="#408080" ALINK="#FF0000">

<TABLE WIDTH="80%" >
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="25%" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><IMG SRC="ashlog1.gif" HEIGHT=59 WIDTH=179>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#8F982C">SERVICES<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+0>-AIMR-<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=-1>QUICK START<BR>
&quot;information we need&quot;</FONT></FONT></B></H1>

<LI><B><FONT COLOR="#408080"><A HREF="quickstart.htm">quick start</A></FONT></B></LI>

<LI><B><FONT COLOR="#408080"><A HREF="index.htm">home</A></FONT></B></LI>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="70%">
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+2>&quot;Quick Start&quot;</FONT></FONT></B></H3>

<CENTER><P>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C">Information We Need To Receive Prior To Our Visit
In Your Office:</FONT><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"> </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">1.A list of all accounts managed specifying which
composite(s) they belong in during each quarter we verify. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">2.For each marketed composite, identify the following:
</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">Market values (in US dollars) on the first and
last day of each quarter for each account. Begin with the first period
of verification and end with the most recent end-of-quarter figures available.
Total return for each quarter for every account in each of your composites.
Note: If segment returns are part of a composite, the segment return, as
well as the cash return, must be provided. Identify which accounts were
revalued due to significant external cash flows. If any, provide the date
of revaluation. Identify which accounts are taxable and which are tax-exempt.
Note: Most firms track this data on spreadsheets. In this case, we prefer
to have an electronic (floppy disk) copy of the spreadsheet. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">3.Please provide us with a primary contact person
to work with during the verification process. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">4.A summary of the market value of all accounts,
by composite, as of December 31 of each year. This summary should reconcile
to the ADV Part I, questions 18 &amp; 19. Please provide a complete ADV
for 1995. For prior verified years, a copy of the pages covering questions
18 &amp; 19 is sufficient. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">5.Indicate which source you use for exchange rate
information (if applicable). </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">6.Copies of the PPS-required footnotes and disclosures
for your marketed composites (including performance). A list of mandatory
footnotes and disclosures is available from AAS, and we can assist you
with their construction.</FONT></P>

<P>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Ashland
Accounting Services, P.C.<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="mailto:info@aascpa.com">info@aascpa.com</A></FONT></FONT></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

