<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#8F982C">SERVICES<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+0>-AIMR-<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=-1>QUICK START<BR>
&quot;for our review&quot;</FONT></FONT></B></H1>

<LI><B><FONT COLOR="#408080"><A HREF="quickstart.htm">quick start</A></FONT></B></LI>

<LI><B><FONT COLOR="#408080"><A HREF="index.htm">home</A></FONT></B></LI>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="70%">
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+2>&quot;Quick Start&quot;</FONT></FONT></B></H3>

<CENTER><P>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C">Information We Will Need For Our Review In Your
Office:</FONT><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF"> </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">1.Coffee (with milk or cream). </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">2.From each marketed composite: </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">Copies of partial or complete bank statements
showing market values of entire accounts and security holdings. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">Copies of reconciliations between market values
on bank statements and values reported to clients from your accounting
system. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">Documentation supporting changes in a client's
guidelines if portfolios were switched from one composite to another, became
fully discretionary, or became non-discretionary. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">3.Copies of selected contracts from pension funds
(list to be provided). </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">4.Invoices from selected accounts or other documentation
to validate that the accounts are fee-paying. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">5.Your Federal Express account number so that
we can expedite the delivery of verification letters when rushed for RFP
deadlines (if applicable). </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">Thank you. We look forward to a long, professional
relationship. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">If you have any further questions regarding our
Quick Start procedures, please feel free to contact one of us at the following
numbers:</FONT></P>

<P>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P>

