<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><B><I><FONT COLOR="#408080"><FONT SIZE=+2>List of Composites</FONT></FONT></I></B>

<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></H2>

<P><BR>
Board of Directors<BR>
Money Management, Inc.<BR>
Street Address, Suite Number<BR>
City, State Zip <BR>
<BR>
The following list of composites is a full disclosure of all composites
managed by Money Management, Inc. and is the representation of management.
<BR>
<BR>
We have examined the following composites beginning start date through
March 31, 1996. Our examination was conducted in accordance with standards
established by the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants and
the Performance Presentation Standards as adopted by the Association for
Investment Management and Research. <BR>
<BR>
Our examination verified that all accounts of the firm were properly included
in at least one of the composites and for the appropriate time periods.
In our opinion, Money Management, Inc. has met the requirements for compliance
to the Performance Presentation Standards. <BR>
<BR>
1.Equity Composite <BR>
2.Balanced Composite <BR>
3.Fixed Income Composite <BR>
4.Asset Allocation Restricted Composite <BR>
5.Client-Specific Mandates Composite <BR>
<BR>
In addition, we have verified the presentations of performance results
of composites numbered one (1), two (2) and three (3). Our opinions regarding
these composites and the mandatory disclosures as outlined by the Performance
Presentation Standards are an integral part of this report. We have not
verified the performance results of the remaining composites, as their
performance is not being presented. The inclusion of such composites is
for disclosure purposes only. <BR>
<BR>
SAMPLE <BR>
<BR>
Ashland Accounting Services, P.C.<BR>
September 30, 1996 </P>

<CENTER><P><BR>
<B>Independent Verification and Attestation for AIMR Performance Presentation
Standards </B>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P></CENTER>

