<TD WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="70%">
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+2>&quot;SAS70&quot;<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=+0>The audit that checks to see if the manager is doing
what they tell you they are doing.</FONT></FONT></B><BR>

<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></H3>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=+1>System controls:</FONT></FONT></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(1) New applications and changes to existing applications
are authorized, tested, approved, properly implemented and documented.
</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(2) Changes to existing system software and implementation
of new system software are authorized, tested, approved, properly implemented
and documented. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(3) Physical access to computer equipment, storage
media, system documentation, and other sensitive areas are limited to properly
authorized individuals.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(4) Logical access to programs and data is limited
to properly authorized individuals. </FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(5) Production processing is scheduled appropriately
and deviations are identified and timely</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">(6) Provisions are developed in case of extended
loss of computer processing capabilities and adequate backups are retained</FONT></P>

<CENTER><P>
<HR SIZE=1 WIDTH="100%"></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><FONT COLOR="#8F982C"><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Ashland
Accounting Services, P.C.<BR>
</FONT><FONT SIZE=-1><A HREF="mailto:info@aascpa.com">info@aascpa.com</A></FONT></FONT></P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>

