 <FONT SIZE="4"><IMG SRC="CDI30E1.gif" BORDER="0"></FONT><FONT SIZE="5"><A HREF="writing.htm">Writing/Editing</A></FONT></B><A HREF="writing.htm"><FONT SIZE="4"></FONT></A></P></CENTER>
<P ALIGN="left"><FONT SIZE="4"><FONT SIZE="4"><I><B>Customer Satisfaction GUARENTEED! If your not happy, we sure aren't happy.</B></I></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="left"><FONT SIZE="4"><FONT SIZE="4"><I><B></B></I></FONT></FONT></P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER="4" CELLSPACING="3" CELLPADDING="3" ALIGN="center" WIDTH="90%">
<TR>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="30%"><B></B>
<P><FONT SIZE="4"><IMG SRC="CDI30E1.gif" BORDER="0"></FONT></P>
<P><B><FONT COLOR="Purple" SIZE="4">Do you need an Internet presence?</FONT></B>
</P>
<P><FONT SIZE="3">Every day more and more large and small businesses are setting up shop with their own Web sites.  If you think that time has come for you, here are a few things you might like to think about first. </FONT>
</P>
<P><B>If you can answer <I>yes</I> to any of the first three questions,</B></P>
<P><B>     </B><FONT SIZE="2"><FONT SIZE="3"><I><A HREF="graphic.htm"><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="CDIF260.gif" WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18"></A></I></FONT>Do you have a mail order catalog or line card? <BR>
     <FONT SIZE="3"><I><A HREF="graphic.htm"><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="CDIF260.gif" WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18"></A></I></FONT>Could your products or services be illustrated on the computer screen? <BR>
     <FONT SIZE="3"><I><A HREF="graphic.htm"><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="CDIF260.gif" WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18"></A></I></FONT>Do your products or services need to be seen to be appreciated? <BR>
<FONT SIZE="3"><I><A HREF="graphic.htm"><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="CDIF260.gif" WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18"></A></I></FONT>Do Internet benefits outweigh costs? What about an e-mail newsletter? And do you have any idea what costs</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2">     might be involved?</FONT></P>
<P>If you can answer yes to any of the first three questions, <B> </B> . . . or if you don't <I>know</I> the answer to the last question, we here at <A HREF="mailto: miseryba@im4u.net"><BR>
Misery Bay Publications</A> can help you now! 
</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="60%"><B><B><FONT SIZE="6" COLOR="Purple">Misery Bay can do it!</FONT></B></B>
<P ALIGN="left"><B><B><I>The advent of relatively inexpensive desktop publishing and HTML-writing software for office 
computers has appeared to place professional publishing within the reach of many small 
businesses. At first glance it often seems like Phyllis the Receptionist should be able to whip up a 
<A HREF="web.htm">homepage</A> or the occasional print <A HREF="writing.htm">newsletter</A> in her free time. Still there are a few things the<BR>
employer must consider before setting Phyllis to work.
</I></B></B></P>
<P ALIGN="left">     First you must ask yourself just how much <A HREF="mbay.htm">free time</A> Phyllis really has. Some of these sophisticated new 
     programs can produce professional-quality work, but they also have a relatively long learning curve. </P>
<P>     And if she has the time to do it, does Phyllis know the difference between hypertext and hyperventilation? 
     Who is going to <A HREF="graphic.htm">screen the photos </A>or produce the <A HREF="graphic.htm">graphics</A>? Phyllis has plenty of clip art, but which graphic 
     tells your story best? Is Phyllis doing both the <A HREF="writing.htm">writing and typing</A>? And would she know an emend if she
     tripped over it?</P>
<P>Our <A HREF="staff1.htm">staff </A>at Misery Bay knows because it's our business to know these things. To examine our 
most recent work on-line check out our  <A HREF="http://www.miserybay.com/bay">Cyber Community</A>. </P>
<P ALIGN="left"><FONT SIZE="4"><FONT SIZE="4"><I><B></B></I></FONT></FONT>And by the way . . . 
if Phyllis really has the time and ability to handle all of the publishing for you, why is she still a receptionist?</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
