<IMG SRC="CDI6131.gif" BORDER="0"></TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="75%"><B>&quot;No matter how good your product, is, if no one knows about it, you 	will never be successful! &quot; Having the best product, the best 	service and the greatest attitude is not; the best sell. But put 	together with the right advertising and marketing strategy, it is! 	It's great we provide our clients with custom made mailing lists, 	but how many times has a client said to you, &quot;I have this great 	product and I know how to sell, but I don't know where to start 	when it comes to putting words on paper, let alone designing a 	brochure or flyer. Can you help me?&quot; Ashley Rose writer, 
	marketing consultant and owner of Rose Publishing in Interlochen	Michigan, can be of assistance. A small business owner for 17 	years, Ashley offers her clients one-stop shopping including 	including lists/services, while specializing in writing, advertising, 	designing  marketing. Using just the right words, Ashley creates 	success for her clients! &quot;I get to know my clients and what their 	needs are. I keep it very simple. I determine WHO they should 
	reach, WHAT they should say and HOW to say it.&quot; Oftentimes, the 	&quot;first impression&quot; is a company's advertisement. Everyone likes 	to look at a pretty face and because businesses are inundated with 	mail, if your advertisement, does not attract and retain the 	reader's attention in the first three seconds, it will not get 
	read. Oftentimes it may never even get opened! You want to &quot;hook&quot; 	the reader (your potential client,) with the first chapter (your 	advertisement) of the book... and by using colors, graphics and 	creative writing, Rose Publishing does just that! Leave the reader 	wanting to hear more... then they  call  you and say &quot;I want what, 	YOU have!&quot; and won't that be nice? Show an &quot;attitude of 	gratitude&quot; and say -&quot;thank you for being my client&quot; to current 	clients offer a &quot;special&quot; to attract, new business.</B>
<P ALIGN="left"><B> Ashley Rose 	of Rose Publishing may be reached at (6l6) 276-9459. </B></P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

