<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Taskforce</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="garden2.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#800040" VLINK="#000080" ALINK="#0000FF">

<MENU><A HREF="index.htm"><img src="dove.gif" align="right" border=0 alt="The Dove of Peace Will Fly"></A>
<CENTER><H1>TASK FORCES</H1></CENTER>
</MENU><CENTER><IMG SRC="bwpeace1.gif"></CENTER><BR>
<H3>Peace Education Center  is an active organization in the Lansing area that is a clearing house for several Task Forces and Work Groups.  Below are several of the areas that they are involved in.  Please check them over and feel free to e-mail your response.</H3>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="fish2.gif"></CENTER>



<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING="4" CELLSPACING="4">

<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD WIDTH=380> <A HREF="church.htm"><IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75
BORDER=0 SRC="church.gif" HSPACE=8 ALIGN=LEFT></A><B><A
HREF="church.htm">NEW! Rebuilding of Churches</A></B> Trying to aid church communities in the south who have lost their house of worship due to prejudices  and ignorance of our fellow human beings.<BR CLEAR=LEFT></TD>


<TD WIDTH=380> <A HREF="simple.htm"><IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75
BORDER=0 SRC="garden.gif" HSPACE=8 ALIGN=LEFT></A><B> <A
HREF="simple.htm">Simplicity</A></B>Gathering the community together to discuss simplicity, how out lives could become simple, how our lives can bring more peace to the earth/world.
<BR
CLEAR=LEFT></TD></TR>




<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD WIDTH=380>
<IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75 BORDER=0
SRC="light.gif" HSPACE=8 ALIGN=LEFT><B>Middle East Awareness Committee</A></B> Providing information and programming on the Middle East from a balanced perspective.<BR CLEAR=LEFT></TD>


<TD WIDTH=380>
<IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75 BORDER=0 SRC="drought.gif" HSPACE=8
ALIGN=LEFT></A><B>Economic Justice</A></B> 
Host of the Fall 95 Economic Justice Conference in Lansing, we now work to assist and network with groups and individuals working on social and economic issues.  Look for a second conference in 1996

<BR CLEAR=LEFT></TD></TR>

<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD WIDTH=380> <A HREF="btl.htm"><IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75 BORDER=0 SRC="tv.gif" HSPACE=8
ALIGN=LEFT></A><B><A HREF="btl.htm">Between the lines</A></B> 
We produce PECs award winning half-hour public access television program, Between the Lines.  Our show airs at 5pm Thursday on WELM cable in East Lansing and Meridian viewing areas as will.  Topics for the 1996 season include the Hunger Strike to Boycott Grapes at MSU and the World Court.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT></TD>

<TD WIDTH=380> 
<IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75 BORDER=0 SRC="flower.gif" HSPACE=8 ALIGN=LEFT><B>
Peace Action Community Education</B>
Based on the knowledge that security at all levels now depends upon care for each other and our common environment and not on military might or violence, we seek to abolish weapons of mass destruction.  We provide educational programming to encourage fair and informed participation in decisions regarding the common good.
<CLEAR=LEFT></TD></TR>

<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD WIDTH=380>
<IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75 BORDER=0 SRC="mask.gif" HSPACE=8
ALIGN=LEFT></A><B>Conflict Resolution</B>
Working to spread knowledge of nonviolent conflict resolution skills throughout the community.  We also work closely with the Michigan Faith and Resistance Peace Teams.
<BR CLEAR=LEFT></TD>

<TD WIDTH=380>
<IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75 BORDER=0 SRC="earth.gif" HSPACE=8
ALIGN=LEFT><B>Teach Peace</B> Fresh from our victory this fall, when we successfully <A HREF="rotc.htm">removed Jr. ROTC from Lansing Area Schools, </A>Teach Peace is now turning our attention to creating alternative educational materials and programs in the schools.  We are beginning to place anti-recruitment materials in the career offices of area high schools as a first step in this new phase of our programming.

<BR CLEAR=LEFT></TD></TR>


<TR VALIGN=TOP><TD WIDTH=380>
<A HREF="newscont.htm"><IMG WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=75 BORDER=0 SRC="bwdove.gif" HSPACE=8
ALIGN=LEFT></A><B><A HREF="newscont.htm"> PEC Newsletter</A></B> 
Peace & Justice News & Views!  The PEC Newsletter currently publishes quarterly, but we hope to expand in the future.  The Newsletter covers PEC events and other peace and justice related stories.  Submit you articles, book reviews, or calendar items and see yourself in print!
<BR CLEAR=LEFT></TD>


<TD WIDTH=380>
</TD></TR>


</TABLE>
<CENTER><H3><a href="mailto:mail@miserybay.com">E-mail the PEC</A> for submission guidelines, to make suggestions or to join our corp of editors!
</H3></CENTER>


</H4><P>
<B><CENTER><H3>Working for Peace with Justice for over 20 years!</H3></CENTER></B>
<CENTER>
<HR ALIGN=center>
