<H1>In This Issue...</H1>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="guatemal.htm">Guatemala</A></H2><B>Jennifer Harbury
is an exciting character. She is a Texas attorney, educated at
Harvard. She was working with Guatemalan refugees fleeing to
the U.S. in the mid-1980s when she decided to go down to Guatemala
to see for herself what was happening. She ended up getting quite
involved in the movement for social justice there and married
Efrain Bamaca, a rebel leader with the ECP (the Guerrilla Army
of the Poor).</b>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="mexico.htm">Government Violence in Mexico</A></H2><B>The Peace Talks between the Zapatista National Liberation
Front (EZLN) and the Mexican government are threatened by six
violent (and in two cases lethal) evictions by state police from
lands that had been occupied since last year by local peasants.</b>

<P>
<H2><A HREF="westbank.htm">Critical Situation in West Bank</A></H2><B>Despite the recent easing of the internal closure of the
West Bank on Saturday, 16 March, the human rights situation in
the West Bank remains critical. </b>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="sweep.htm">Sweep of Birzeit University </A></H2><B>In the early hours of the morning,
at least 370 Palestinians in the villages of Birzeit, Abu Qash,
and Abu Shukhaydim were roused from their sleep and taken from
their homes in the largest Israeli raid since the signing of the
Oslo Accords.</b>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="grape.htm">Grape Boycott</A></H2><B>On February 13, 1996, six students began a water-only fast, which lasted six days. They placed their
lives in danger to focus attention on the many reasons why we
must boycott grapes. </B>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="landmine.htm">Action alert: Landmines</A></H2><B>The Peace Education Center is one of the listed national sponsors supporting an international
ban on landmines.</B>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="tax.htm">WHERE YOUR INCOME TAX Money Really Goes:</H2></A><B>The Government Deception and what you can do about it.</B>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="coord.htm">Coondinator's Corner</A> </H2><B>Allow me to introduce myself: my name is Amy Cairns. The
Board welcomed me to the Peace Education Center as coordinator
in mid-January. </B>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="btl.htm">Between the Lines </A></H2><B> Between the Lines, the award-winning cable television program
produced by the Peace Education Center has begun its 1996 season
with 1 series of programs dealing with issues of peace and justice
and how they relate to the Lansing area community. </B>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="volunter.htm">Volunteers</A></H2><B>&quot;People say, what is the sense of our small effort.
They cannot see that we must lay one brick at a time, take one
step at a time.&quot; -- Dorothy Day</B>
