<br clear>
<!-- END HEADER -->


<BODY>

<P><CENTER>
<H2>Support Landmine Ban</H2></CENTER>
<P>
<H3> The Peace Education Center is one of the listed national sponsors supporting an international
ban on landmines.</H3>
<P>
<H3> Given the apparent momentum in the shifting of U.S. government
policy on the landmines issue and the reconvening of the CCW Conference
in Geneva at the end  of April, it is especially important to urge a total ban on
anti-personnel landmines.</H3>
<P>
<H3> Please write or phone these key individuals and if possible,
send copies of your letters to US Campaign to Ban Landmines, c/o
VVAF, 201 S. Street, N.W., suite 740, Washington, DC 20009.</H3>
<P>
<H3>President Bill Clinton
<br>
<H3>The White House
<br>
1600 Pennsylvania Ave, NW
<br>
Washington, D.C. 20500
<br>
Phone:202-456-1111</H3>
<P>
<H3>The Honorable Warren Christopher
<br>
Office of the Secretary of State
<br>
2201C Street, NW
<br>
Washington. D.C. 20520
<br>
Phone: 202-647-6575</H3><CENTER>
