<HEAD><TITLE>Peace Education Center Newsletter - Coordinator's Corner</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="moon2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#804000" LINK="#3141CE" VLINK="#408080">
<a name="top"><!-- HEADER -->
<A HREF="index.htm"><img src="dove.gif" align="right"border=0 alt="The Dove of Peace Will Fly"></A>
<br><hr size=4>
<br clear>
<!-- END HEADER -->


<BODY>
<IMG SRC="angel.gif"ALIGN=left>
<P>
<H2>Coordinator's Corner</H2>
<P>
<H3>Greetings!</H3>
<P>
<H3> Allow me to introduce myself: my name is Amy Cairns. The
Board welcomed me to the Peace Education Center as coordinator
in mid-January. I am having a wonderful time and have enjoyed
meeting many of you already.</H3>
<P>
<H3> For those of you I haven't met, I'11 tell you a little about
myself and the work I will be doing here at the Center.</H3>
<P>
<H3> I first came to the Lansing Area as a student at MSU, over
five years ago. I was active on campus with many women's organizations,
as well as serving in a series of appointments with the University.</H3>
<P>
<H3> I have also been deeply involved with the Mid-Michigan Clothesline
Project, a project focusing on violence against women. We have
traveled throughout Mid-Michigan, spoken at academic conferences,
to classrooms, and been featured in several local journals and
in the press.</H3>
<P>
<H3> In addition to Clothesline Project programming and publicity,
I have been involved in some freelance projects as well, such
as speak-ins, the Celebration of Audre Lorde evening of poetry
and film and Sexual Assault Awareness Month activities. I bring
with me varied skills and experience from my years as a campus
activist.</H3>
<P>
<H3> I currently work ten hours a week at the PEC. With your help,
I am looking forward to making 1996 a truly great year for peace
and justice in the Lansing area.</H3>
<P>
<H3> My work will concentrate on improving office accessibility
and resource materials as well as working with the membership
and coordinating volunteer efforts.</H3>
<P>
<H3>I believe that the next year will be pivotal to the future
of the Greater Lansing community and I know that working together
we can succeed in creating the type of community in which we all
want to live.</H3>
<P>
<H3> I am generally in the office on Mondays and on Wednesday
afternoons. The rest of my schedule tends to shift based on the
needs of volunteers and other members. I look forward to meeting
you.</H3>
<P>
<H3>In Peace,</H3>
<P>
<H3>Amy Cairns</H3><CENTER><IMG SRC="fish2.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER><A HREF="newscont.htm"><IMG SRC="tealprev.gif"></A></CENTER>
