<HEAD><TITLE>Peace Education Center - Where Tax Money Really Goes</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="money.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3141CE" VLINK="#408080">
<a name="top"><!-- HEADER -->
<A HREF="index.htm"><img src="dove.gif" align="right"border=0 alt="The Dove of Peace Will Fly"></A>
<!-- END HEADER -->

<H1>The Government Deception</H1>
<P>
<IMG SRC="tax02.gif" HSPACE=1.5 ALIGN=right>
<H3>The pie chart  is the Administration's view of the budget
(and similar to the figures you'll see in your IRS booklet or
the media). This is a distortion of how our income tax dollars
are spent because it includes Trust Funds (e.g., Social Security)
and buries the expenses of past military spending in nonmilitary
parts of the pie. For a more accurate representation of how your
Federal income tax dollar is really spent, see the large chart.</H3>
<P><CENTER>
<A HREF="tax.htm"><IMG SRC="tealprev.gif"></A></CENTER>
