<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Peace Education Center - Where Tax Money Really Goes</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="money.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3141CE" VLINK="#408080">
<a name="top"><!-- HEADER -->
<A HREF="index.htm"><img src="dove.gif" align="right"border=0 alt="The Dove of Peace Will Fly"></A>

<!-- END HEADER -->

<CENTER>
<H2>WHAT YOU CAN DO</H2></CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><H3> Refuse to pay the 3% federal excise tax on your phone bills.
This tax has been used symbolically as a 
war tax since World War I. Nonpayment of the federal tax is
between you and the IRS and should not 
result in cut-off of phone service. Though illegal, non-payment
of the tax is almost risk-free. The thousands of people now refusing
this tax have made it virtually uncollectible. <EM>Please contact
us for more details.</EM></H3>
<LI><P>
<LI><H3> Refuse to pay all or part of your income tax. Though illegal,
thousands of Americans are openly participating in this form of
protest. You can take control of your paycheck and avoid contributing
to the military. Contact us for information or referral to a war
tax resistance counselor near you.</H3>
<LI><P>
<LI><H3>Contribute resisted tax money to an organization working to
help people (e.g., day care centers, health clinics, food banks,
housing programs, international human rights organizations) or
to an alternative fund which pools tax money from resisters and
gives grants to human needs and peace groups.</H3>
<LI><P>
<LI><H3>Demonstrate and leaflet on April 15 at the IRS or a post office
where returns are mailed at the last minute.</H3>
<LI><P>
<LI><H3>Develop a community of support for those doing or contemplating
war tax resistance. Resistance is Strengthened if people can remove
the sense of iso lation and talk about their fears about resistence.
 Contact us for groups in your area.</H3></UL>

<H3><EM>Write for more information to the addresses or contact the</EM><CENTER>
National War Tax Resistance Coordinating Committee<BR> PO Box 774<BR>
Monroe, ME 04951 (800)269-7464<BR><EM> email:</EM> nwtrcc@igc.apc.org.</H3></CENTER>
<CENTER><P>
