<HEAD><TITLE>Clinton County Courthouse Timeline</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="kacki.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#800000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800040">
<P>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC="courth1.gif" HSPACE=1.5 ALIGN=right>
<H1>Clinton County Courthouse</H1>

<H2>Early Timeline</H2>

<UL>
<LI><H4>1855, October - question of moving county seat to St. Johns first discussed </H4>
<LI><H4>1856, December - county offices moved to Plumstead Hall in St. Johns</H4>
<LI><H4>1858 - A 20 x 25 foot brick county building erected on the northwest portion of the public square</H4>
<LI><H4>1869 - taxpayers approve a $25,000 building proposal 1,734 to 1,170</H4>
<LI><H4>1869, October - building committee approves plan based on Bay City Courthouse</H4>
<LI><H4>1869, fall - cornerstone laid and foundation completed</H4>
<LI><H4>1871, March 15 - courthouse dome struck by lightening causing damage estimated between $250 and $500.</H4>
<LI><H4>1872, January 8 - building committee submits final report to supervisors</H4>
<LI><H4>1904, December 31 a new $1,000 Seth Thomas tower clock set to ring in the new year</H4>
<LI><H4>1927, spring - extensive remodeling done to the interior including the addition of a fireproof vault</H4>
<LI><H4>1957, spring - general renovation costing $20,000 took place. The entire exterior sandblasted</H4>
<LI><H4>1958 - new entrance built for $59,089.51. Judges chambers added.</H4>
<LI><H4>1965 - a west wing built at cost of $165,765.56</H4>
<LI><H4>1966 - matching east wing constructed for $246,000</H4>
<LI><H4>1969 - supervisors room in the west wing transformed into a District Court. Supervisors move into the east wing basement civil defense area. Two rows of rear seating removed from Circuit Court for conference and office rooms</H4>
<LI><H4>1974 - District Court moved to Whittemore Street</H4>

</UL>

