<H2>Pardon Our Dust . . .</H2><P><HR><P>
<H1>STATUTES OF THE NATIONAL FRATERNITY</H1>
<B>of the</B>
<H2>SECULAR FRANCISCAN ORDER</H2>
<B>in the<B>
<H2>UNITED STATES OF AMERICA</H2>

<H3>TABLE OF CONTENTS</H3>

<H4>SECTION I

<P>
Organization and Structure
<MENU>
<LI>Article 1     National Fraternity
<LI>Juridical person                   
<LI>Guided bythel\llinisterand aCouncil
<LI>Organization and functions 
<P>Article 2     Governing Bodies 
<LI>National Fraternity Council
<LI>National Executive Council
<LI>Conference of National Spiritual Assistants
<p>Article 3     National Fraternity Council Composed of
<LI>International Councillor 
<LI>Business of the National Fraternity                
</MENU>

<P>
National Fraternity Council has legislative, deliberative and
elective powers 
<LI>Regular meeting of the National Fraternity
<LI>National Fraternity Council meets for elections every three
years 
<LI>National Fraternity Council may meet at other times during
any year
<LI>National Fraternity Council duties 
<MENU>
<LI>Promote secular Franciscan spirituality
<LI>Prepare for celebration of national elections
</MENU>

<LI>Search out, identify, publish and distribute materials for
formation

<LI>Compose Regional Fraternities 
<LI>Inform appropriate religious Superiors of creation of Regional
Fraternities and seek spiritual assistance
<LI>Maintain liaison with Presidency of the International Council
OFS            
<LI>Elect US representative to the International
<MENU>
<li>Set amount of annual financial contributions to NAFRA from Regional Fraternitites
<LI>Resolve and clarify inquiries and/or problems 
<LI>Provide practical and pastoral interpretation of General
<LI>Constitutions and these statutes                         
                  
<LI>Consult with Conference of National Spiritual Assistants
concerning composition of Regional Fraternities
<LI>Approve composition of Regional Fraternities
<LI>Such other duties set forth in Article 66    , Sec (c) 
(e), (h), (i), (j), (k), and (I), of the General Constitutions
</MENU>

<P>
Article4     Structure for Property Control                   
  <LI>NAFRA is incorporated                                    
                                 
<LI>Elected officers of the National Fraternity Council shall
function as corporate officers                           
                                                           
                    
<LI>Financial books and records of the corporation to be
maintained by National Treasurer and to be open for
inspection                                               
<LI> Upon termination of corporation, all assets, along with
its library and records, shall become the property of the
&quot;juridic person immediately superior,&quot; ie     Secular
Franciscan Order                                         

<P>
Article 5          National Executive Council                  
<LI>Between meetings of the National Fraternity council, an
elected National Executive Council shall carry on business
             
<LI>Composed of National Minister, National Vice Minister,
National Secretary, National Treasurer, at least one elected
Councillor, President of the Conference of National Spiritual
Assistants, and the International Councillor             
<LI>All members of the National Executive Council have voting rights                                                       
<LI>Procedure for election of the members of the National
Executive Council                                            
<LI>Duties of National Executive Council                         
                                                           
<li> Appeals from decisions of dismissal from membership
rendered by Regional Executive Councils                               
              <P>
 Article 6         Duties of Officers of the National Executive
Council               
<li>      The National Minister                                  
                                                             
                               
<li>
      The NationalVice Minister                              
                                                             
                                      
<li>
      Should the office of National Minister become vacant, the

    National Vice Minister shall succeed                     
                                                             
          
<li>
      The National Secretary                                 
                                                             
                                           
<li>
      The National Treasurer                                 
                                                             
                                             
<li>
      International Councillor                               
                                                             
                                                 
<li>
      President of Conference of National Spiritual Assistants
        <P>
 SECTION II
<P>
 <LI>Voting and Conduct of Business
<P>
 Article 7 Convocation      , ,                              
                                                             
                                             
<LI>Regular meeting of the National Fraternity shall be the annual
meeting ofthe National Fraternity Council
<MENU>
<LI>National Executive Council meets
<LI>National Fraternity Council meets for the purpose of elections
once every three years                                   
    
<LI>National Congress at least once every five years
</MENU>

<LI>Minister of each Regional Fraternity receives at least two
months


<P>
Article 8 Voting Rights

<LI>Minister of each Regional Fraternity has the Primary
Responsibility
<LI>When Regional Minister is impeded from attending         
                  
<LI>No Region may cast more than a single vote               
                        
<LI>Each person may cast only one ballot


<P>
Article 9         Quorum; Majority; Counting Ballots; Procedure
<P>
<LI>Quorum consists of majority of number enrolled as attending
the meeting                                                  
                                                             
                                                           
<li>
      Absolute majority is fifty per cent (    50%) plus one of
the total   number     Relative or simple majority is the highest number
of votes cast
<LI>Where questions arise concerning procedure               
                                   


<P>
Article 10     Elections                                     
                                                             
                                                        
<li>National Fraternity Council elects National Minister, National
Vice Minister, National Secretary, National Treasurer, at
least one Councillor the International Councillor and a substitute
delegate for the International Councillor                  
<LI>According to the norms of the law of the Church, of the General
Constitutions for the Secular Franciscan Order of 1989, and
of these statutes                                        
                                                             
                                                     
<LI>Each elector shall submit one vote     Then all ballots, including
blanks, shall be counted for the purpose of calculating the
number which shall constitute a majority                 
     


<P>
Article 11     Convocation and Nominations                   
                                                         
<li>
         Executive Council shall appoint chairman for Nominations
Committee                                                    
                                                             
                                                             
    
<li>
Eligibility as candidate for election to office              
                                     
<P><HR><P>
 
<LI>Minimum age for permanent, temporary profession          
             
<LI>Period of inquiry not less than six months
<LI>The period of candidacy shall consist of not less than
twelve (12) months and not more than thirty-six (36 )
months                                                   
                                                             
                                                             
                         
<LI>Process of formation in the United States will be conducted
according to norms established by the National Fraternity
Council                                                  
                                                             
                                                             
                          



Article 20 Transfer, Withdrawal, Suspension and Dismissal
from the Fraternity and from the Order                   
                                  

<LI>Articles 55 - 59 of General Constitutions govern these
matters

Article 21       Regional Fraternity                     
                                                             
                                  


<li>Each Regional Fraternity is composed as such by the
National Fraternity Council of NAFRA                     
                                                  
<LI>A juridical person                                       
                                                             
                                                
<LI>Region animated and guided by a Regional Minister
and Council which is duly elected                        
                                                             
       
<LI>Organized and functions in conformity with the Rule,
the General Constitutions, the Ritual, and these Statutes

<LI>Has powerto enact individual norms                       
                                                
<LI>National Fraternity Council shall confer with the Conference
of National Spiritual Assistants, to inform them of the
composition of each Regional Fraternity, and to seek
appropriate spiritual assistance

<LI>Governing bodies of each Regional Fraternity
Conference of Regional Spiritual Assistants exercises
pastoral care and spiritual guidance in regard to each
Regional Fraternity                                          
                                                         
                                              
<li>
Regional Fraternity Council                                  
                                                             
                    
<li>
      Composition                                            
                                                             
                                                             

<li>
      Representative organ of all of the fraternities which
   together compose the Regional Fraternity
<li>
     Duties                                                  
              
<MENU>
    <LI>The Regional Minister

</MENU>
<P>
     <LI>Regional Executive Council Composition:

<MENU>
    Regional Minister, Regional Vice Minister, Regional
  Secretary, Regional Treasurer, at least one elected
  Councillor, and the President of the Conference of
   Regional Spiritual Assistants                             
                                                             
<LI>     Regional Executive Council shall meet at least twice a
   year at time and places to be determined by its members 
<li>
     Duties of Regional Vice Minister, Secretary, and Treasurer
   shall follow the model set forth in that portion of these
   Statutes which deals with the National Fraternity         
                    
<LI>     National Fraternity policies and procedures to be followed
   in the event of resignation or removal from office on the
   part of any elected officer                               

</MENU>                                                             
                                    
<li>
     Structurefor Property Control                           
    
<MENU>                                                      
<li>
     Responsibilities of the National Fraternity shall apply
   to the Regional Fraternities                              
                                                             
                                     

<LI>Audit shall be performed at least every three years      
                       
<LI>Expenses of Regional Fraternity Minister and members of
Regional Executive Council, including those members who
have been appointed but serve without vote, shall be borne
by the Regional Fraternity for their attendance at all
meetings                                                 
                                                             
                                                             
                             
<LI>Regional Fraternity is responsible for contributing to the
National Fraternity on a fair share basis from its common
fund to underwrite the cost of that fraternity           
                                           
</MENU>

<li>
Fraternal and Pastoral Visits                                
        
<MENU>                                             
<li>
Regional Executive Council shall make its requests of the
National Minister and of the Conference of National
Spiritual Assistants for fraternal and pastoral visits   
                          
<LI>At the time of fraternal and pastoral visits, and also when
presiding over and witnessing elections, Regional
Executive Council shall present to NAFRA officers and
to delegates of the President of the National Conference
of Spiritual Assistants an appropriate stipend           

</MENU>                                        
Article 22     Amendments, interpretation of Statutes    
                        

<LI>Done by two-thirds vote of the National Fraternity Council
    
<LI>Subject to the approval of the International Presidency  
  
<LI>Interpretation shall be by rules of canon law, civil law
where applicable, and may have recourse to Robert's
Rules of Orderin regard to procedural matters            
                                        
<LI>ADDENDUM: Wherever there appears in the above
Statutes the word &quot;Region&quot; or &quot;Regional,&quot;
&quot;Province&quot; or
&quot;Provincial&quot; may also be used until Provinces cease
to exist, at which time provision shall lapse               
                                                  
</MENU>
