<a name="corp"></a>
<h3>Corporate Profile</h3>

<blockquote>Entech Engineering was formed in 1980 by a group of experienced professional engineers.  Initial projects addressed the so-called energy "crisis" by assisting clients to analyze and take control of energy costs.   </blockquote>

<blockquote>
From that beginning, ENTECH (from ENergy TECHnology)  evolved over the past 16 years to become a fully integrated engineering/architectural firm of 68 individuals performing repeat business for dozens of clients, primarily in the eastern US.  Some clients have invited us to work with them in other regions of the US, such as the Midwest, Arizona and California.  </blockquote>

<blockquote>Our in-house full time staff includes the disciplines of electrical, mechanical, structural, civil, architectural and environmental.  The design teams are strengthened by 20 registered professionals, architects and engineers, who are supported by designers, drafters, marketing and  administrative personnel.</blockquote>

<blockquote>Entech is widely recognized in the state of Pennsylvania for energy consulting, facilities design, water and waste water system design.  Our firm has worked with 30 colleges and universities, 15 municipalities along with several dozen industries and hospitals in the eastern US. </blockquote>

<blockquote>Each of the business units is managed by business unit directors who are responsible for marketing, client relations, design and project management within the unit.  Resources are freely used across units to best serve the client's need for a particular project.</blockquote>

<blockquote>In the area of TQM, Entech embarked on a total quality program in 1992 and to date has spawned over 30 teams, most comprised of a broad cross-section of company staff.  Teams investigate and recommend continuous improvement ideas in all areas - design, client relations, fee basis, CAD systems, marketing, benefits and human resources.</blockquote>
<a href="#top">Back to top</a>

<a name="mission"></a>
<h3>Our Mission</h3>

<blockquote>Our mission is to provide consulting, engineering and other related professional services that meet or  exceeds our client's expectations.   This mission is based on a shared set of values  at Entech: client satisfaction, uncompromising ethical standards, teamwork, professional development, community involvement.</blockquote>

<blockquote>We help clients achieve succesful projects by working closely with them in a partnering relationship from day one.  We help to define goals, schedule and budget the project and then communicate that to the various constituencies.  We can also bring financing sources to bear in combination with traditional engineering and architectural services, project management and startup assistance to achieve project goals and to stay within budget.</blockquote>

<blockquote>Entech's solid background in energy systems analysis and design is a part of everything we do, on all projects.  We know that 90% of the cost of a project comes in the long term operation and maintenance of the facility.  For that reason, we design systems that are sensitive to O&M costs as well as capital costs and aesthetics.  We look hard at life-cycle costs and work to minimize those costs through prudent design combined with energy saving materials for the structure as well as the systems.</blockquote> 
<a href="#top">Back to top</a>


<a name="special"></a>
<h3>Specialty Areas</h3>

Entech over the past 16 years has developed expertize in several areas: 
  <UL>
           <LI> <b> Energy audits and analysis</b> - with over 50 million square feet of buildings analyzed, Entech knows how to help companies control energy costs.  With more experience in this area than any other firm in the eastern US, we have established data bases and approaches to analyzing cost savings and cost payback for any type of building.  With the current trend to increased competition in the utility industry, Entech can help in determining the correct electric utility rate for your operation.</li><p>

           <LI>  <b>Facility Audits</b> - An emerging market for Entech and a natural extension of the extensive energy auditing experience of Entech, we offer facility auditing for institutions and organizations.  The facility audit allows the client to prioritize and plan future facility upgrades.  The audit is a survey of the entire facility, including architectural and all building systems.  These are examined for current conditions, expected remaining life and projections for planning for the future.  Call us for more information on how we can apply our experience to help you plan future cash flows for building and system maintenance through a well conceived and documented facility audit.</li><p>

           <LI><b> Fluid flow modeling, heat transfer, analysis.</b>  Entech has performed a number of studies for clients who have problems with fluid flow.  Whether heat flow from a delicate clean room process, or water flow in a potable water or fire system with numerous branches, reservoirs and tanks, Entech can analyze the system and recommend various options for improvement that will help your organization. </li><p>

           <LI> <b><a href="commer.html">Plant Expansion and Renovations</a></b> -  combining the full talents of the firm to  renovate or build a facility that will meet your needs for the future.  For industrial expansion, we will work with your process consultant to design the foundations, building shell, exterior treatments, heating, ventilating, air conditioning, electrical power, communications, security, plumbing, etc.  </li> <p>

             <LI> <b>International </b>- Entech is engaged in an association with an organization in Hungary looking into appropriate technology to handle the problem of wastewater disposal in widely dispersed villages in the country. </LI><p>

              <li> <b><a href="munic.html">Water and Wastewater Systems</a></b> - Entech has performed studies and designs for many municipalities and industrial clients to meet their potable water needs and to treat their waste water. </li><p>

               <li> <b><a href="dereg.html">Electric Deregulation Studies</a></b> - With Pennsylvania on the forefront of utility deregulation, we are helping clients analyze the impact of deregulation so that they can operate more cost effectively in the future. </li><p>


</UL>
<a href="#top">Back to top</a>

