<HEAD>
<TITLE>Entech Engineering - Technical Hot Links </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="entback.gif" BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF>
<IMG SRC="graphics/entechw.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><H1>Tech-Links</H1>
<H5>January 1997</H5>
<HR>
<CENTER><H5>Technical links for engineers, architects, building managers, contractors and building owners</H5></CENTER>

<HR>
<UL>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.aecinfo.com/">The AEC InfoCenter</A>... rated among the Top 5% of all web sites.You'll find links to materials suppliers, architecture schools, building code updates, and too much else to mention. The site comes from Canada, so the building codes and real estate info have a limited audience; but most other information crosses the border well. Includes listing of architects, engineers along with the master spec catalog library.  The Building Product Library is categorized by CSI/CSC 16 Division MasterFormat. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.aecnet.com">The AECNET</A>... Connect to engineering resources on the net using their free downloadable bulletin board software.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.aecsystems.com/">A/E/C Systems International</A>...It's a trade show on your computer.  This site also provides conference programs for the real shows, with interactive registration forms. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.acec.org">American Consulting Engineers Council</A>...the voice of the consulting engineer in business.  Find out how legislation affects your firm, participate in programs and seminars that help you do your business better.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.aia.org/">American Institute of Architects</A>... home page for the AIA, trends in architecture, education, careers in architecture, selecting an architect.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.ansi.org/">American National Standards Institute (ANSI)</A>...Web site describes the Institute and offers a searchable catalog (available for purchase) of the approved American National Standards.  For International Standards check out <A HREF="http://www.iso.ch/welcome.html">International Organization for Standardization</A>. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.asce.org/">American Society of Civil Engineers</A>...describes the organization's publication, membership, education opportunities, and other technical, professional and educational activities. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.astm.org/">American Society for Testing and Materials</A>...ASTM's Web site describes the Society's products, services, standards, technical publications, conference, statistical quality assurance programs, technical and professional training courses, and it presents a director of testing laboratories. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.iconservices.com/amyworld/amyworld.html">Amy's World</A>...has nothing to do with anything technical. Amy is one of our mentor kids who has her own page and she wanted you to see it. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Art/Architecture/">Arts: Architecture</A>...An index to worldwide resources of construction data, library and museum achives, and individuals' Web sites. <P>


<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.plannet.com/desktop.html">Architect, The Wired</A>...Interesting set of links and information for architects and designers including <A HREF="http://www.plannet.com/1990ADA.txt"> ADA Text Online</A>, the complete text of   PUBLIC LAW 101-336JULY 26,1990  AMERICANS WITH DISABILITIES ACT OF 1990.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.nscee.edu/unlv/Libraries/arch/rsrce/webrsrce/index.html">Architecture and Buildings</A>...An extensive list of research sources with links to Web sites related to architecture, engineering, construction, real estate, housing, urban planning, energy, government standards, exhibits, and publications, with links to AEC-related discussion groups and Telnet links enabling users to log into the catalogs of other architecture libraries nationwide.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.afsonl.com/">Architects' First Source</A>...First Source Online is the electronic complement to the Architect's First Source print publication.  The site includes links to manufacturers' sites, journal articles, and searches by subject and CSI classification. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.architect.org/">The Architecture Research Institute</A>...The Institute's Web site describes the organization's three components - the Advanced Studies Center, the Media Center and the Public Education Center. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.appa.org">Association of Higher Education Facilities Officers</A>...the premier organization of college and university facilities managers - offers education and networking for the people operating and maintaining the infrastructure of institutions of higher education.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.awma.org">The Air and Waste Management Association</A>...a professional association of people in industry, government and academia working on air pollution and waste management issues.  The site offers information about publications, meetings, chapter groups, and employment and professional development.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.buildernet.com/index.html">Builder Net</A>...compendium of resources for people in the building industry.<P>


<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.buildingspec.com/index.html">Building Spec</A>...a set of catalogs for the design professional and building manager.  Includes boilers and water treatment equipment at this time, with plans for expansion into all areas of Master Spec designation equipment and related specifications.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.cadonline.com/">CADALYST Magazine</A>...Web site features industry news and technical information for AutoCAD user, with tips and viewpoints from technical experts.  For another CAD site take a look at<A HREF="http://www.awa.com/nct/software/cadlead.html"> WorldCAD Access</A>...WorldCAD Access is part of NCT Web Magazine with newsletters, bug list for AutoCAD Rel 13, product reviews and related CAD articles.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.building.org">Construction: The Building Industry Exchange</A>... A non-profit, interactive exchange center exclusively for building industry businesses and professionals. BIX is a clearinghouse of educational, communication and informational resources and offers instant access to industry businesses, people, publications, products, and employment opportunities worldwide.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.csinet.org/">Construction Specifications Institute</A>...information about Institute and its services <P>


<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.ei.org">Engineering Information Village</A>... Engineering information, links to documents and journals for engineering related articles.  "<EM>Our task has been to identify, organize and facilitate easy access to the published engineering literature of the world."</EM><P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.englib.cornell.edu/">The Engineering Library at Cornell University</A>...includes <STRONG>ICE</STRONG>, Internet Connections for Engineering, a  catalog of Engineering-related resources on  the Internet , and the <STRONG>Gateway</STRONG>, a catalog of engineering references at the Mann Library.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.csa.com">Environmental RouteNet</A>...a service of Cambridge Scientific Abstracts, offers environmental regulation updates, access to environmental data sources, and 40 - 60 relevant environmental news items each day from the major news wires.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.fmlink.com/">FMLink</A>
...This site provides easy access to facilities management and real property information. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.gcn.net/">Global Construction Network </A>...A listing of member contractors along with news for contractors.  Check out <A HREF="http://www.gcn.net/arena/arena2.html">The Ice Palace Project in Tampa</A>,for an example of how the world wide web can be used to coordinate project design and construction involving several different firms, in different locations in the US. Site progress photos, location maps; the partnering process explained.  A practical use for the web. Too bad they are not keeping it up to date!!!<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.aecnet.com/IES/ieshome.html">Illuminating Engineering Society of North America</A>...The IES publishes over 80 documents including the popular IESNA Lighting Handbook.
By the way, check out <A HREF="http://www.aecnet.com/lightnet/searchmen.html">LightNet </A> which lists hundreds of lighting manufacturers by name and address for which  you can do a product search.
Another good lighting page is <A HREF="http://www.ge.com:80/gel/index.html">The GE Lighting Home Page</A>which gives you a tour of the GE Lighting Institute and has been rated as one of the top 5% web sites. See also <A HREF="http://www.englib.cornell.edu/ice/lists/illuminating-engineering.html">Cornell University links to Illuminating Engineering</A> at other universities.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.ipr.com/">InterPRO-AEC</A>
...InterPRO services include helping firms create and manage their own Web site and do business on the Internet. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.ifma.org/">The International Facility Management Association</A>
...site describes facility management issues, lists chapters, events, publications, and services. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.ieee.org">Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers</A>...The home page for electrical engineers.  Access to standards and a description of the IEEE, the world's largest technical professional society.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.clr.toronto.edu:1080/VIRTUALLIB/larch.html">Landscape Architects Reference </A>...pages of interest to landscape architects<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.wpi.edu/Depts/Academic/Fire/Nfpa/nfpa_home.html">National Fire Protection  Association (NFPA)</A>...Membership information; publications, etc.  NFPA publishes life safety 101 and the National Electrical Code - in both hardcopy and on CD-ROM. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.nist.gov/">National Institute of Standards & Technology (NIST)</A>...this site offers a comprehensive overview of NIST research, service, facilities, and programs for industry. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.nspe.org">National Society of Professional Engineers </A>...NSPE is the national engineers organization.  The page offers information to prospective engineers and practicing engineers; continuing education offerings; NSPE products and services.  Plus there will be links to independent job information home pages.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.pspe.org">Pa Society of Professional Engineers</A>...PSPE home page featuring information about the society, an Affiliate of the National Society of Professional Engineers. Features a section on continuing education for engineers across the state; up-to-date legislative and business news; electronic job posting among other areas of interest to the engineering community.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.engr.psu.edu/www/coe/engr-facts.html">Penn State - Engineering</A>...how could we leave this out since one in fifty engineers in the US is a Penn State Grad - besides they have the best football team in the country!!<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.dep.state.pa.us">Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection</A>... weekly "update" newsletter listing grants,  pending legislation and regulations, workshops and seminars, etc.  Good links to all sorts of environmental information in the state and around the country.   See also <A HREF="http://gwrp.cciw.ca/index_e.html"> Groundwater Remediation</A> references from Canada.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.dcnr.state.pa.us">Pennsylvania Department of Conservation and Natural Resources</A>...The part of the former PA DER that looks after our 114 state parks.  Includes local maps for "rails to trails".<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://http://arioch.gsfc.nasa.gov/wwwvl/engineering.html#listing">Plant Engineer</A>...Technical articles, jobs, vendor listings, consultant listings, special feature articles of interest to engineers who work in manufacturing or chemical processing plants. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.rsmeans.com/">R.S. Means</A>
...provides construction cost information products and services. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.rfweston.com">Roy F. Weston Company</A>...Lots of good technical advice and links for people in the environmental field.<P>


<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.sme.org">Society of Manufacturing Engineers </A>...SME represents the engineers in industry. <P>


<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.swe.org/">Society of Women Engineers</A>...encourages women to achieve full potential in careers as engineers and leaders; expands the image of the engineering profession as a positive force in improving the quality of life, and demonstrates the value of diversity to the engineering profession.  See also <A HREF=" http://tweedledee.ucsb.edu/~kris/WIS.html">Women in Science and Engineering</A><P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.specs-online.com/">Specs-Online</A>...connects architects, engineers, and specifies to building product manufacturers with Internet Web sites. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.sweets.com/">Sweet's Group Online</A>...offers detailed product data, current market trends and topics, and discussion forums. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.usace.army.mil/sad/regvilg.htm">U.S. Army Corps of Engineers</A>...South Atlantic Division <P>


<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://mr2.wes.army.mil/">Tri-Service CADD/GIS Center</A>...features Center-related announcements, demonstrations, technical papers, CSDD details and standards. <P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.epa.gov">The US Environmental Protection Agency</A>...Access EPA, a directory of data bases,  EPA scientific models, information on state environmental libraries, and descriptions of products and services.<P>

<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="http://www.ce.gatech.edu/WWW-CE/home.html">The Virtual Civil Engineering Library at Georgia Tech</A>...a comprehensive list of WWW servers containing information about Civil Engineering, including Gopher servers and FTP archives.  Includes universities, organizations, government agencies, and commercial sites from around the world. A gem of a site for civil engineers. <P>



</UL>
<CENTER><H5>Return to <A HREF="index.html">Entech's Home Page</A></H5>
<P>

<CENTER><H5>If you find a web page that you think should be here,   <A HREF="mailto:TMcMahon@entecheng.novell.net"> e mail  </A> us the web address and we'll add them to the list.</H5> </CENTER>

<H5>Comments or suggestions: e mail to..<A HREF="mailto:TMcMahon@entecheng.novell.net">Tom McMahon</A></H5>
</CENTER>
