<P>At Entech, we employ a wide range of disciplines to fill the many needs of our clients.  If you are a motivated enthusiastic individual looking for a challenging and rewarding position in the Architectural/Engineering field, the Entech team would like to hear from you.   We offer a competitive benefit package, salary commensurate with experience.  We are presently looking for qualified individuals for the following positions.  

<P><B>Architectural Positions</B>	 - All positions filled at this time.

<P><B>Electrical Positions</B> - All positions filled at this time.

<P><B>Mechanical Positions</B> - All positions filled at this time.

<P><B>Civil/Structural</B> 

<P><EM>Environmental Engineer:</EM>  Entry level position.  Four year degree in civil or environmental engineering.  EIT certification desired.  For design of water/waste water treatment systems.  Must be computer literate, and possess both oral and written communication skills. 

<P><EM>Resident Project Representative: </EM> For projects in Schuylkill County, Pennsylvania.  One to Four years in construction field observations.  Knowledge of construction techniques, practices, and provisions of contract documents.  Oversees work and material to be incorporated in the projects to conform to specifications.  Conducts site inspections.  Verifies tests, equipment, startup and training are conducted with appropriate personnel.  Maintains records/files and prepares reports. 

<P><B>Environmental</B>  - All positions filled at this time.

<P><B>Project Management</B> 

<P><EM>Project Manager:</EM>  10 years experience in facilities projects with 5 years project management experience.  College/University background desired.  P.E. or R.A. and good communication skills required.

<P><B>Construction Management</B> - All positions filled at this time.

<P><B>Administrative</B> - All positions filled at this time.	
<P>Decisions on summer employment will be made in April 1997.

</p>

