<A NAME="toby"></A>
<TABLE WIDTH=591 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=4 WIDTH=590 HEIGHT=20>
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=4 WIDTH=590 HEIGHT=5>
	<IMG SRC="graphics/590x5.gif" BORDER=0>
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=4 WIDTH=590 HEIGHT=20>
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	<IMG SRC="graphics/toby100.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100>
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Tobyhanna Depot <UL>
	<LI><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Steam Distribution System
	<LI><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Coal-fired steam generators</H4></UL>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="http://www.iconservices.com/entech/index.html">
			<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond1.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="http://www.iconservices.com/entech/index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
		<P><STRONG>Tobyhanna Army Depot</STRONG> requested <STRONG>Entech</STRONG> to conduct two consecutive comprehensive studies at the Depot. <EM> First,</EM> evaluate the existing high pressure steam distribution system.<EM> Second</EM>, study the coal-fired steam generation systems to determine options for the most economical way of extending the Depot's operations.<P>  After receiving the top performance award from the Army in 1994, Tobyhanna is looking for more ways to improve their quality for the next 20 years. 

<P>The systems have been in operation since 1952 when the Depot was first constructed and are no longer capable of supporting the Army's electronics missions with reliability.  <STRONG>Entech </STRONG> used a value engineering approach to the problem while considering the merits of various alternatives.  The prime finding was that the decentralization of steam production, coupled with alternative methods of generating heat, would allow the Army to maintain operational readiness while reducing the taxpayers expense in operating costs. <P> 

Upon completion of the studies, the Depot asked <STRONG>Entech</STRONG> to produce designs to replace the coal boiler and prepare bid documents in less than four months.  The <STRONG>Entech</STRONG> team responded and did the job on this tight time schedule.  <P>

Under the direction of <A HREF="mailto:DHaldeman@entecheng.novell.net">Dwight Haldeman</A>, the <STRONG>Entech </STRONG>team designed the estimated $14 million decentralization of the steam system which included six major boiler rooms, with a combination of 18 boilers ranging in size from 100 Hp to 600 Hp.<P>  

In addition, air rotation units were incorporated into six buildings, each 200 ft by 1200 ft.  The combination of units will be capable of circulating 3,120,000 cubic feet of air per minute; the rough equivalent of completely changing the air in the Astrodome every 15 minutes. 

<P>The design included opportunities to select from several potential fuel sources; natural gas, propane or oil. Each system is configured to maintain a 30 day strategic reserve capacity.  <STRONG>Entech's</STRONG> involvement produced quality improvements in readiness, reliability and operating costs.
		
		<P><A HREF="#top">Return to the top</A>
	</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>





