<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
		<P><STRONG>Entech </STRONG>performed a number of designs for the Letterkenny  Army Depot over the last several years.  These included upgrades to electrical and fire protection systems covering 120,000 sq ft area in two buildings; improvements to the fire protection systems in two additional buildings, and a high speed fire alarm system.

<P> At the wastewater treatment plant, <STRONG>Entech</STRONG> designed repairs to sludge handling equipment .  At the water treatment plant, we replaced flocculators, mixers and sediment tank flow meters.

<P>Under the government's EEAP (Energy Efficiency Analyses Program), <STRONG>Entech </STRONG>completed a comprehensive lighting study at the Letterkenny Depot.  The study covered more than 70 buildings, totalling over 1.8 million sq. ft.   Field data including utility bills were collected and analyzed using <STRONG>Entech's</STRONG> extensive library of utility rate analysis programs. The   incremental demand and usage charges were identified and presented to the Army to form the basis of a post- wide energy management strategy. 
		<P><A HREF="#top">Return to the top</A>
	</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>






