<HEAD>
<TITLE>Picatinny Arsenal</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ff ff ff" LINK="#FF 00 00 " VLINK="#FF 00 00">
<TABLE WIDTH=591 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=3 WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
	<TD WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4>Picatinny Arsenal:
	<BR>Service Water System Audit
	<BR>Field Testing</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../munic/index.html">
			<IMG SRC="../graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../munic/index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>

<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
	
	<P><B>Hydraulic Model:</B> Entech was contracted by the U.S. Army Mobile Corps of Engineers to complete an energy audit of the arsenal's service water system. The arsenal-wide computer modeling of the service water system consists of 35 miles of mains ranging from 2" to 12", three wells, pump stations, storage tanks and standpipes.

	<P><B>Field Testing:</B>  A field testing program is included in conjunction with the modeling, consisting of:
</UL>
<LI>calibration of master water supply meters
<LI>three-point performance tests for all high service pumps
<LI>20 flow tests to develop representative C-factors for water mains
<LI>25 fire hydrant flow tests to determine adequacy of fire protection
<LI>20 hydraulic gradient tests along major and minor distribution routes
<LI>10, 24-hour per day trunk main gauging
</UL>

	<P>Utilizing the results of the field testing, coupled with the determination of the future water requirements, the model will be utilized to evaluate required improvements and possible water conservation opportunities.
		</P>


<p><a href="../munic.html">Return to the Municipal list</a> </p>
