<P>

<STRONG>Official Sewage Facilities Act 537 Plan Update</STRONG>:</b> Prepared in 
accordance with August 1992 revisions to PA DEP guidelines, a plan 
identifying schedules and costs for addressing sewage needs of the entire 
township. Plan included a treatment plant to serve  existing dwelling 
units experiencing septage system malfunctions and developing on-lot 
management programs for areas of the township.	

</p>
<p><b>Official Sewage Facilities Act 537 Plan Update:</b> Prepared update in 
accordance with Chapter 71 Regulations. The update identified 
schedules and costs for addressing the sewage needs of the Township. 
The identified project includes treatment plant, pump stations and 
collection lines to serve several areas of the Township.	</p>
<p><b>Butler Township Sewer Project:</b> Prepared financial assistance 
application through the Farmers' Home Administration and secured a 
$2.1 M grant and a $4.6 M loan at 5.25% interest for 40 years. Funding 
will allow design, engineering and construction of a 
sewer system which includes 70,000 lineal feet of collection lines, a .25 
MGD sewage treatment plant and six pump stations to serve 980 
equivalent dwelling units in the Township. Responsibilities will include 
design of STP and gravity lines, preparation of bidding documents, user 
fee calculations, FmHA reports and closing documents, interim financing, 
permit preparation, construction observation and processing contractor 
payment request. Estimated Project Cost: $8.1 M.	</p>
