	<HR>

	<P><B>Official Sewage Facilities Plan:</B> Prepared update in accordance with Chapter 71 regulations for the City of Reading and the associated service area of its 28.5 MGD sewage treatment plant.  Municipalities included in the plan consist of:  Cumru Township, Muhlenburg Township, Spring Township, Kenhorst Borough, Laureldale Borough, Mohnton Borough, Mount Penn Borough, Temple Borough, Wyomissing Hills Borough and City of Reading.	

	<P><B>Infiltration/Inflow:</B> Retained to performed the infiltration/inflow and collection system analysis portion of the city's wastewater system enhancement. Work includes installation of flow meters in each of the three drainage areas of the city, a review of flow records from contributing municipalities to the city wastewater facilities, identification of "fast-track" areas where rehabilitation can proceed prior to a full-fledged study, and preparation of a completion report defining a program for city-wide infiltration/inflow reduction.  The study was authorized in February 1995, and is expected to be complete in January 1997.  One of the areas prioritized for immediate action is an 18 inch diameter sewer main where flow projects from outlying municipalities indicate a need for sewer relief within the next three years.

	<P><B>Sewage Works Upgrade and Expansion Program:</B> Grants Management related to the $31 million upgrade and expansion of the City of Reading 28.5 MGD sewage treatment plant. Included in the work performed for the city are the following services:
<UL>
<LI>		 	Construction Grant Management
<LI>		 	PENNVEST Management
<LI>		 	Mercury Clean-up and Remediation
<LI>		 	Wasteload Management Reporting
<LI>		 	Bio-solids Analysis
<LI>		 	Pump Station Evaluation
<LI>		 	Development of Plans of Study
</UL>
	<P><B>Sewage Plant Operations Analysis:</B> Review operations of the 28.5 MGD City of Reading sewage treatment plant and make recommendations for plant improvements.
	<P>
		

