	<P><B>Official Sewage Facilities Act 537 Plan Update:</B> Finalized the Act 537 Plan for the Township including the identification of additional alternatives to provide sewers to a portion of the Township.  Analysis of alternatives included estimated user fee comparisons, funding options, construction schedules and future service projections.	

	<P><B>Seltzer/Woodland Acres Sewer System:</B> Design and engineering services during construction of a gravity/pump station sanitary sewer system project to serve over 300 homes which utilized a "wildcat" system.  Responsibilities included preparation of bidding documents, user fee calculations, PENNVEST application preparation, PENNVEST reports and closing documents, construction status reports and processing of contractor payment requests.  Project Cost: $1.6 M

	<P><B>Beach & Kimberly Streets Sewer Extension:</B> Prepared and secured financing from the Department of Community Affairs which resulted in a grant covering 80% of the project cost.  Project included the development of specifications, construction observation and liaison between owner, contractor and financial institution.  Sewage conveyance provided to 13 EDU's.  Project Cost:  $0.09 M.	

	<P><B>Mar Lin Sewer Project:</B> Prepared financial assistance application through the Farmers' Home Administration and secured a $0.43 M grant and a $0.6 M loan at 5% interest for 40 years.  Funding will allow the design and engineering services during construction of a sewer system which includes collection and conveyance system and two pump stations to serve 155 equivalent dwelling units in the Township.  Responsibilities will include design of gravity lines, preparation of bidding documents, user fee calculations, FmHA reports and closing documents, interim financing, permit preparation, construction observation and processing contractor payment request. Estimated Project Cost: $1.1M	

	<P><B>Official Sewage Facilities Act 537 Plan:</B> Prepared in accordance with August, 1992 revisions to the PA DEP guidelines, a plan identifying schedules and costs for addressing the sewage needs of the Borough.  The identified project included a 0.2 MGD treatment plant and 55,000 feet of collection lines.
	</P>

