	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4>Pennsylvania Energy Office:
	<BR>Energy Analysis - 
	<BR>Wastewater Treatment Plants</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../munic/index.html">
			<IMG SRC="../graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../munic/index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>

<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
	
<P><B>State-wide Energy Analysis, Pennsylvania Wastewater Treatment Plants:</B> Entech completed a state-wide project that analyzed energy usage at 1,300 wastewater treatment plants.  The first phase included mailing a survey for data-gathering; the second phase involved in-depth studies of 16 high-cost plants.  The most common opportunity for improvement involved the use of variable frequency controlled motors.  Other program phases included preparing a financial analysis manual, design of a $20,000 demonstration plant project, development of a procedure for calculating savings, reports and several presentations.  The project was completed in 1991, with a fee of $57,000.
</p>

<p><a href="../munic.html">Return to the Municipal list</a> </p>
</TD>
</TR>
