<HEAD>
<TITLE>Rush Township</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ff ff ff" LINK="#FF 00 00 " VLINK="#FF 00 00">
<TABLE WIDTH=591 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=3 WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
	<TD WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4>Rush Township:
	<BR>Act 537
	<BR>FmHA Loan Application</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../munic/index.html">
			<IMG SRC="../graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../munic/index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>

<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
	
	<P><B>Official Sewage Facilities Act 537 Plan Update:</B> Prepared update in accordance with Chapter 71 Regulations; project included evaluation of feasibility of connection of 250 existing dwelling units to low pressure sewer system, development of on-lot management program and ordinance requiring hydrogeologic studies for lot sizing and routine pump-outs, and preparation of capped sewer ordinance.

	<P><B>Lake Hauto Pressure Sewer System:</B> Design and engineering services during construction of a pressure sewer system to serve 300 homes in a lake-side community experiencing on-lot system malfunctions.  Responsibilities included preparation of bidding documents, user fee calculations, PENNVEST application preparation, PENNVEST reports and closing documents, construction status reports and processing of contractor payment requests.  Project Cost: $2.2 M.	

	<P><B>Official Sewage Facilities Act 537 Plan Update:</B> Prepared update in accordance with Chapter 71 Regulations; project included evaluation of feasibility of connecting and treating 150 existing dwelling units including an industrial user.	

	<P><B>Quakake/Tamanend Sewer Project:</B> Prepared financial assistance application through the Farmers' Home Administration in order to secure financing for the design and engineering services during construction of a sewer system.  Projected financing includes a $0.6 M grant and a $1.2 M low interest loan.  Funding will allow design of a sewage collection system, a 0.9 MGD sewage treatment plant and two pump stations to serve 150 EDU's in the Quakake/Tamanend area of the Township. Estimated Project Cost: $2.1M

	<P><B>Hometown Sanitary Sewer Improvements Program:</B> Entech prepared an amendment to the Rush Township Act 537 Plan to allow for five extensions to the existing sanitary sewer system to be constructed.  In addition, the amendment provided for miscellaneous infiltration/inflow (I/I) work to be conducted in the existing system along with the installation of a parallel relief sewer line to address a surcharge condition in the main interceptor of the system.

	<P>The amendment was approved by the PADEP and the RTSA authorized that Entech proceed with the design and the preparation of an application to PENNVEST for financing for the project.

	<P>The total project is estimated to cost $2.1 million and is expected to take one year to complete.  A total of 90 EDU's will be served by the sewer extensions, with over 10,000 LF of sewer line and four pump stations.  The I/I work will involve televising and grouting of existing lines, manhole rehabilitations and line replacements.  Estimated Project Cost: $2.1 M
		</P>

<p><a href="../munic.html">Return to the Municipal list</a> </p>
</TD>
</TR>
