	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4>White Haven Municipal Authority:
	<BR>Engineer of Record
	<BR>DEP Reporting</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../munic/index.html">
			<IMG SRC="../graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../munic/index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>

<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
	
	<P><B>Engineer of Record for the White Haven Municipal Authority:</B> Duties are to prepare the Annual Wastewater Management Report to the Department of Environmental Protection, provide professional advice at monthly authority meetings, assist in negotiations with developers and adjacent municipalities on sewage conveyance and treatment agreements, and provide assistance in operations and maintenance of the treatment plant and collection system.

	<P>The collection system consists of approximately 30,000 feet of sanitary sewage pipe, ranging in diameter from 8 to 12 inches.  The treatment plant, rated at 340,000 gpd, is an activated sludge-extended aeration type; sludge is treated by aerobic digestion, dewatered in a plate and frame filter press.  The system currently serves the Borough of White Haven and the adjacent developed portion of Dennison Township.  During the past year, negotiations for sewer extensions have been occurring with neighboring East Side Borough and Foster Township.
		</P>
<p><a href="../munic.html">Return to the Municipal list</a> </p>
</TD>
</TR>
