<TITLE>Bloomsburg University Page</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ff ff ff" LINK="#FF 00 00 " VLINK="#FF 00 00">
<TABLE WIDTH=591 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=3 WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
	<TD WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	<IMG SRC="graphics/150x15.gif" BORDER=0 WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
<!--	<IMG SRC="graphics/bloom.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100> -->
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Bloomsburg University
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Halls and
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Rec Facility</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">
			<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
		<HR>
		<B>Schuylkill Hall:</B>Provided design services to upgrade electrical distribution, lighting, telephone and data systems. Provided plans for replacement of lighting fixtures, distribution panelboards, motor control centers, receptacles, outlets and bran
ch wiring. Receptacles and data outlets added to students room to accomodate student computer use.

		<P><B>Women's Collegiate Varsity Softball Field: </B> Provided plans and specifications for the construction of a new women's collegiate varsity softball field which included a unique 30-foot high backstop, dugouts and lighting.  The campus is quite com
plicated topographically and this presented challenges to Entech in locating and designing this large, flat area.  Services included submission of plans to the local conservation district and the local municipality for review of the regrading which was ra
ther significant.

		<P><B>Hot Water Storage Tank Replacement:</B> Provided plans and specifications for bidding and construction of the removal of existing domestic hot water storage tanks and installation of new tanks located in two dormitory buildings.  Although construc
tion was completed over the summer months of 1994, one of the dormitories was occupied and construction sequenced so that one of the tanks was operational at all times.  Entech services include construction observation.

		<P><B>Elevator Upgrade Project:</B> Elevators in three dormitories were upgraded over the summer months of 1994.  Two dormitories utilize hydraulic and traction elevators and two of the three were occupied during construction.  Entech provided specifica
tions for competitive bidding and also provided construction observation services.

		<P><B>Carver Hall:</B> Renovations included air conditioning the second and third floors.  Innovative design used an ice storage system that provides chilled water to the entire building. Significant advantages are that a 20 yr old chiller was replaced 
with a slightly smaller unit, which in combination with the ice storage system, provides air conditioning for the entire building. 

		<P><B>Renovations to Four Buildings:</B> Provided design services which packaged various renovations to four buildings.  Design included new offices in Nelson Field House, ADA bathroom renovations in Montour Hall (dormitory), ADA elevator upgrades in tw
o dormitories and new roof and parapet installations on Northumberland Hall.  These projects were completed August 1993.

		<P><B>Electrical Renovations to Montour Hall:</B> Provided design services for renovation and upgrade of the electrical distribution and lighting systems for Montour Hall.  Project included replacement of existing light fixtures, replacement and additio
n of distribution panelboards, replacement and addition of receptacles in each dorm room, the installation of a data cabling system to each dorm room, and the modifications to eight dorm rooms and two bathrooms for ADA compliance.

		<P><B>Dining Facility - Scranton Commons:</B> One addition featured a solarium roof structure; the other three story addition accommodated a faculty dining area and the President's Dining Room.  Engineering and design included the relocation of steam, c
ondensate, electrical, stormwater, sanitary and gas and water piping systems.

		<P><B>Student Health and Recreational facility:</B> Performed feasibility study for a new 80,000 sq feet building. Worked with staff, students and faculty to find suitable site; prepared plans and cost estimates for long range planning purposes.
<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A>		
	</TD>

