	<H4><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Bryn Mawr College
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Campus-wide Power Factor Study
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Halls and Buildings</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">
			<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>

<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
	<B>Dalton Hall:</B> Engineering and design for new sprinkler system and new alarm system.  
	<P><B>Park and Life Sciences Bldg:</B> Heating, ventilating and air-conditioning system analysis to identify deficiencies, recommend improvements, evaluate HVAC alternatives for energy cost savings.  Provide proper ventilation in all rooms and provide ai
r conditioning in all rooms not currently served by the central system.
	<P><B>Power Factor Study Campus Wide:</B> Low power factor caused excessive penalties on the electrical bills. Entech recommended changes to improve overall power factor to 95%.  Payback period for the modification was 11 months.
	<P><B>Graduate School of Sociology: Sick Building Syndrome: </B>Entech did an investigation of foul odors eminating from within the building and found two sources; (1) a formaldehyde type odor due to a bee killer spray/ plastic components located inside 
a window air conditioning unit.  (2) A number of sewer traps were in a "dry trap" condition due to non use of certain drains over a period of years.  Alternative recommendations were proposed for solution to both of these problems.
	<P><B>Graduate School of Sociology: ADA Compliance: </B>Entech performed an ADA analysis for the bathrooms in the building and determined the actions required to make the facilities handicapped accessible.  The Feasibility Study included design and costs
 for all improvements and modifications to bring the bathrooms into full ADA compliance. 
	<P> <B>Merion Hall Residence Building: </B>Performed engineering and design of main distribution panel; addition of new 75 Kva transformers; removal of the existing 208/120 v panels and feeders and replacement with new panels for each of the four floors 
of the building.  Entech prepared documents for bidding the project.  Construction  began in May of 1995. 
	<P> <B>Gymnasium HVAC and Power Requirements :</B>In preparation for the visit of President Clinton on Dec 13, 1993; Entech reviewed the existing HVAC and electrical distribution system in the gym to determine if the system was adequate for the anticipat
ed crowd. With modification and some temporary equipment, the systems were ready for the visit and performed according to plan..
	<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A>
	</TD>
