<HEAD>
<TITLE>Cabrini College Page</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ff ff ff" LINK="#FF 00 00 " VLINK="#FF 00 00">

<TABLE WIDTH=591 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=3 WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
	<TD WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	<IMG SRC="graphics/150x15.gif" BORDER=0 WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	<A HREF="graphics/cabrini2.jpg"><IMG SRC="graphics/cabrini.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100></A>
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4><BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Campus-wide Facilities Audit
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>and ADA Survery</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">
			<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
		<HR>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="graphics/newcab.gif">
</CENTER>
		<P><B>New Residence Hall: </B> Provided architectural and engineering design services for the construction of the College's new three-story, 120 student apartment style residence hall.  The new facility will accommodate four, five and six students per a
partment with a common kitchen and living room in each apartment.  Construction consists of masonry load bearing walls, concrete plank floors, two-pipe heating and cooling system with gas-fired boilers and a complete fire protection system.  Each floor of
 the residence hall will have a common study lounge.  Project cost is projected to be approximately $4 million including site development.  Construction is expected to be complete by March 1997.

		<P><B>Mansion:</B>  Provided engineering and design services for the rehabilitation of the existing heating system and the addition of a central air conditioning system.  Work consists of replacing the steam boilers with new gas-fired hot water boilers,
 steam radiators serving convent area to be replaced with two pipe fan coil units to provide both heating and cooling. Existing steam heating coils and air handling units will be replaced with new hot water units, installation of a new chiller and modific
ations to the existing 5 KV switchgear required to support the Mansion.  Project costs are projected to be $550,000 with renovations to be complete by October 1996.

		<P><B>Campus-Wide Energy Audit:</B> Conducted an Energy Audit for seven (7) of the campus buildings totalling more than 266,000 S.F. of gross building area.  The energy evaluation covered all energy systems including outside lighting.  Entech identified
 twenty-five (25) Energy Conservation Opportunities (ECOs).  The estimated construction cost for the twenty-five (25) ECOs was approximately $87,000.  The estimated annual energy savings were $22,000 resulting in an average simple payback period of 4.1 ye
ars. 

		<P><B>Campus-Wide Stormwater Collection Improvements:</B> Conducted a preliminary engineering analysis and completed design services for upgrades to the existing campus stormwater collection system.  Construction began in March 1996 with construction co
sts estimated to be approximately $75,000.

		<P>All systems were evaluated for construction costs, comfort, energy consumption, operating and maintenance costs, and expected service life.  Feasibility Study was completed in September 1994.  Entech recommended the installation of direct expansion u
nits.  Construction costs are estimated to be approximately $560,000 with annual cooling costs of $54,000.  Entech is currently providing design services and construction is expected to be complete for the 1997 cooling season.

		<P><B>Sacred Heart Hall Computer Learning Center:</B> Provided architectural design for Sacred Heart Hall that included installation of a new ceiling, soffits and lighting.

		<P>Cabrini College requested Entech to conduct a campus-wide Facilities Audit and ADA survey encompassing more than 370,000 ft of gross building area. The Facilities Audit provided a source for identifying the existing physical condition and functional
 performance of buildings and infrastructure, as well as maintenance deficiencies.  From the information gathered and presented by Entech, the College was able to estimate capital renewal and replacement requirements for individual projects and	annual for
ecasts. 

		<P>The<B> Facilities Audit </B> provided the College with a basis for decision making on routine maintenance, capital renewal/deferred maintenance, functional improvements, replacements and disposal of the College's facilities. 	The results of Entech's 
effective Facilities Audit will extend the useful life of the facility, reduce 	disruptions in use of space and equipment downtime, and improve relations between facilities management departments and facilities users.

		<P>Audit Completed January 1995
		<P>
		<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A>
