	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
		<HR>

	<B>CHESTNUT HILL COLLEGE</B>, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.

	<P><B>Energy Audit - Main Physical Plant:</B> Entech conducted an Energy Audit for the main physical plant.  The energy evaluation covered all energy systems including outside lighting.  Entech identified the following three (3) Energy Conservation Oppor
tunities (ECOs): 1) Summer Shutdown; 2) Boiler Plant Improvements; 3) Boiler Plant Lighting.  The estimated construction cost for the three (3) ECOs was approximately $97,000.  The estimated annual energy savings are $43,900 for a 14% reduction from curre
nt energy expenditures.  This saving yields an average simple payback period of 2.2 years.

	<P><B>Energy Conservation Measure Grant Application Submission:</B> Entech completed and submitted Energy Conservation Measure (ECM) Grant Applications to the Pennsylvania Energy Office for Cycle XVI funding for the three (3) ECOs.  Entech was successful
 in obtaining an ECM Grant for all three (3) ECO projects.  The total grant amounted to over $74,000.

		<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A>
