<TITLE>Cheyney University Page</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ff ff ff" LINK="#FF 00 00 " VLINK="#FF 00 00">
<TABLE WIDTH=591 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=3 WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
	<TD WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	<IMG SRC="graphics/150x15.gif" BORDER=0 WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
<!--	<IMG SRC="graphics/cheyney.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100> -->
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Energy Analysis at
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Cheyney University
	</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR>
	<TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">
			<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
	<B>Technical Assistance - Energy Analysis: </B>Entech performed a T/A study and grant application in 1991 	and later provided the audit of nineteen buildings (842,300 sq ft).  Energy evaluation included all energy systems.  A total of 51 Energy Conservat
ion opportunities were identified which when totally implemented, can result in a annual energy savings of $490,000 with a simple payback period of 3.2 years.
	<P>The University elected to implement the Summer Shutdown recommendations as the first step in the program. 

	<P><B>Ada S. Georges Dining Hall and Marcus Foster Student Center: </B> Provided mechanical and electrical design services to renovate the kitchen facilities.  Work consisted of installation of new kitchen hoods, new filters, lights, fire suppression sys
tem, new hood support system, new gas service, and ductwork modifications to increase make-up air.  The survey covered more than 100,000 GBSF.

	<P><B>Replacement of Steam and Condensate Lines:</B> Provided engineering and design services for the replacement of approximately 225 L.F. of five (5) inch underground high pressure steam piping and associated three (3) inch condensate return piping.  T
he steam lines are located between Baily Hall and Marcus Foster Student Center.

	<P><B>Cooling Load Calculations and Alternate Cooling Systems Analysis:</B> Developed cooling load calculations and recommendations for the replacement of cooling systems for the following three (3) buildings: 1) McKnight-Rogers; 2) Baily Hall; and 3) Ca
rnegie Library.  Based upon the cooling load calculations, Entech concluded that the existing air conditioning equipment located in Baily Hall and Carnegie Library were of proper size and a recommendation for a one-for-one replacement was made.  The cooli
ng load calculations for McKnight-Rogers indicated that the existing air conditioning equipment and supporting ductwork were severely undersized.  Entech recommended a complete system replacement with a complete packaged variable air volume system includi
ng roof top unit and insulated duct system.  Construction costs are estimated to be $150,000.

	<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A><P>
	</TD>
	</TR>
