	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	<A HREF="graphics/stroud2a.jpg"><IMG SRC="graphics/stroud2.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100></A>
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
		<H4><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>East Stroudsburg University
		<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Koehler Field House Lighting Project</H4>
	</TD>
</TR>
<TR>		
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
		<HR>
		<A HREF="http://www.esu.edu">East Stroudsburg University</A> commissioned Entech to perform a 
		campus-wide energy study.  Based on the recommendations from this study, ESU proceeded with the 
		design and construction of lighting improvements in the Field House and Natatorium.
		<P>In the Field House, 120 mercury vapor fixtures were replaced with more efficient metal halide fixtures. 
		The light 	fixtures specified were designed to partially illuminate the ceiling indirectly.  With the repainting 
		of the ceiling, the Field House now has a bright, more even, non-glare lighted environment.
		<P>In the Natatorium, the existing mercury vapor fixtures wre also replaced with metal halide fixtures. 
		The fixtures were realigned using the results of a lighting distribution modeling program, allow better 
		access for maintenance of the lamps and ballasts.
		<P>The project was completed in January 1992.  Total cost of the project was $120,000, with annual 
		energy savings of approximately $35,000.
		<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A>
	</TD>

</TR>
