<HEAD>
<TITLE>Indiana University of Pennsylvania Page</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ff ff ff" LINK="#FF 00 00 " VLINK="#FF 00 00">
</TABLE>
<TABLE WIDTH=591 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=3 WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
	<TD WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	<IMG SRC="graphics/150x15.gif" BORDER=0 WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	<A HREF="graphics/iup2.jpg"><IMG SRC="graphics/iup.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100></A>
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Indiana University of Pennsylvania
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Coal-Fired Boilers Replacement Project</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">
			<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
		Entech conducted an energy audit of Indiana University of Pennsylvania's (IUP) central steam boiler plant which consists of four (4) coal-fired water tube boilers each rated at 30,000 lbs/hr. The average annual steam production is approximately 102,700 lbs of steam. The University's cogeneration plant was also evaluated since the cogeneration plant provides steam to make up shortages during peak demands. 
		<P>Entech recommended the replacement of two existing coal-fired boilers with two new gas-fired 30,000 lbs/hr boilers. Entech was retained to provide design and construction services for this project. The design included the demolition and removal of the two existing coal-fired boilers, adaptation of new boilers to existing systems and structures including foundations, piping interfaces, breaching connections, new electrical connections, fuel supply lines, local and remote (cogeneration plant) controls, lighting and equipment access to the building.
		<P>Construction costs are anticipated to be approximately $800,000, with expected energy savings of $185,000 per year and a simple payback period of 4.3 years. Entech was successful in obtaining an energy grant from the Pennsylvania Energy Office in the amount $75,000 to offset the cost of this project. 

		<P><B>Robert Shaw Building</B>:

		<U><EM>Steam Boiler Replacement.</EM></U>  Provided engineering and design services for the replacement of one 58 KW electric steam boiler with a new gas-fired steam boiler rated at 280 MBH input.

		<U><EM>Lighting Retrofit.</EM></U>  Provided engineering and design services for the replacement of 34 watt fluorescent luminaires and 400 watt low halide luminaires with new 400 watt high-bay metal halide light sources.

	<P><B>Wahr and Langsham Halls: </B> Provided engineering and design services to modify the existing heating systems to provide a uniform distribution of heat throughout the buildings.  Work consisted of modifying distribution piping to replace the direct return system with a reverse return system, rebalancing the distribution piping systems, replacement of steam to hot water converters with new exchangers and replacement of distribution pump impellers and motors.

	<P><B>Stouffer Hall:</B>  Provided engineering and design services for the replacement of one 150 ton centrifugal chiller with a new 150 ton screw chiller and the replacement of the existing cooling tower.

	<P><B>Honors College:</B> Provided concept design, design development and contract documentation for a 9,000 SF Honors College with an existing dormitory; project involved:  alterations and upgrades to all resident rooms, elevator replacement and full electrical upgrade; development of five classrooms.

		<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A><P>
	</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
