<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Kutztown University Page</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ff ff ff" LINK="#FF 00 00 " VLINK="#FF 00 00">
<TABLE WIDTH=591 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=3 WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
	<TD WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	<IMG SRC="graphics/150x15.gif" BORDER=0 WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	<IMG SRC="graphics/kutz.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=100>
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Kutztown University
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Campus-wide Electrical Study
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Campus energy audit
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>EMS Design</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">
			<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
	<B>Campus-wide Electrical Study: </B>Entech provided engineering services for the upgrade of the entire electrical 	distribution on campus. Scope included preparation of the feasibility for a complete replacement of the electrical 		distribution system.  The campus' 5kV distribution system was eliminated and incorporated into the new 13.2 kV system.  	Project involved installation of new outdoor walk-in 15 kV vacuum switchgear, upgrading of the 2.4 kV distribution systems 	in nine buildings, replacement of 2.4 kV and 15 kV power feeders, modification of existing underground distribution duct 		system including manhole expansion and duct installation.
	<P><B>Campus energy audit: </B>Entech performed an audit of all 29 buildings on campus and assisted the University 		in implementing the 18 energy conservation measures recommended.  The University realized over $600,000 savings 		per year as a result of the $1.4 million project. In the Spring of 1989, both Entech and the University were publically 		recognized for their roles in energy conservation by receiving the Governor's Energy Award, one of only three given in the 	state of Pennsylvania.

	<P><B>EMS Design:</B> Entech prepared design documents for bidding of the new energy management system for the 	campus.  The 800 point system was partially funded by a $100,000 ICP grant from the Pennsylvania Energy Office based 	on an application prepared by Entech. 
	<P><B>Miscellaneous campus projects:</B> Entech assisted the University with the boiler summer shutdown 		project, improvements to the boiler plant, the design of a pool dehumidification system, underground storage tank 	removal, improvements to the North Parking lot, feasibility study for the student union building, analysis of the structure of 	the stadium press box and campus-wide storm water evaluation.

	<P><B>Heritage Center:</B>

		<P><EM>Farmhouse Renovations - </EM>Provided engineering and design services for the repair of all deteriorated wooden structural members located in the Farmhouse basement along with the installation of new concrete footers for new structural supports and a new concrete slab.  These modifications were required in order to preserve the structural integrity of the 100-year-old stone farmhouse.

		<P><EM>Underground Electrical Ductbank -</EM> Provided engineering/design services for the installation of approximately 600 L.F. of an underground concrete encased high voltage/communication ductbank to support the University's Pennsylvania German Heritage Cultural Center.  Total project costs were approximately $130,000.

		<P><EM>Sanitary Sewage Collection and Conveyance System -</EM> Provided engineering, design and construction services for the installation of a sanitary sewage collection and conveyance system. Project costs were approximately $110,000.

		<P><EM>Barn Roof Rehabilitation - </EM>Provided architectural design services for the rehabilitation of the cedar shake barn roof.  Specific work included repair of all damaged structural members, replacement of missing structural ties, and the replacement of existing roof trusses, sheathing, cedar shakes and related items.  Total project costs were approximately $75,000.

		<P><EM>Construction Services -</EM> Provided construction services for various projects located at the Heritage Center.  Projects included new electrical underground ductbank, new sanitary sewage collection and conveyance system, barn roof rehabilitation and the construction of a new visitor's center.

		<P><B>Rugby Field: </B> Provided surveying services regarding the development of a new rugby field.  Grading, erosion and sedimentation control plans were also developed.  The site for the new rugby field was previously utilized as a dumping site for clean fill from various University capital improvement projects.

		<P><B>South Dining Hall Refrigeration System Replacement:</B>  Conducted a feasibility study  to determine the most appropriate refrigeration replacement system. Entech recommended the installation of a new central system.  Entech provided the engineering and design services for the new central system along with the design for a new mechanical equipment room to house the new central system.

		<P><B>Maintenance Building Boiler Replacement and UGST Removal:</B> Provide engineering, design and DER certified inspection services for the removal of one 500 gallon No. 2 heating oil UGST along with the installation of a new gas-fired boiler.

		<P><B>Central Boiler Plant Conversion Feasibility Study:</B>  Entech evaluated the central steam plant's current operations and prepared a comprehensive plan for future operations.  Entech's evaluation included code requirement analysis, steam demand calculations, fuel selection options, equipment life expectancy, environmental compliance, operating cost development, life cycle economic analysis, and identification of O&M impact associated with options recommended.

		<P><B>Comprehensive Campus-Wide Facilities Audit:</B>  Entech is currently conducting a campus-wide facilities condition survey.  The audit will cover approximately 1.8 million GBSF comprised of more than 42 buildings.  The facilities audit will provide the University with a source for identifying the existing physical condition and functional performance of the buildings and infrastructure, as well as maintenance deficiencies.  From the information gathered during the audit, the University will be able to estimate capital renewal and replacement requirements for individual projects and annual forecasts.

		<P><B>Campus-wide Square Footage Survey: </B> Conducted a square foot survey of the entire campus.  Entech physically measured every building and room on campus.  Survey comprised more than 1.8 million GBSF consisting of more than 42 buildings.  Entech developed a database for sorting and generating SSHE reports.

		<P><B>Title V Air Quality Compliance Survey:</B> Conducted an air emissions inventory of nitrogen oxides (NOX), sulfur dioxide, carbon monoxide, particulates, volatile organic compounds (VOCs) and 189 hazardous air pollutants (HAPs).  The purpose of the survey was to determine the University's "Potential to Emit" any of these compounds and to determine which PADEP operating permit is applicable to the University.

	<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A>
	</TD>

</TR>
</TABLE>	
