	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
	<B>Environmental Assessment: </B>Entech performed an environmental assessment of a suspected contaminated area on the campus and designed a remediation system based on the the Pump and Treat process.  The  system as installed consists of a granular activ
ated carbon filtering system which treats the water through a series of activated carbon bed reactors and re-injects the filtered water back into the ground to provide for remediation of both soil and groundwater.
	<P><B>Campus Storm and Sanitary System: </B>Entech provided engineering services to evaluate the separation of the existing combined sanitary/storm water sewer system.  Services included site surveys, smoke tests, listing of plumbing code compliance issu
es, construction cost estimates, and a detailed report indicating the condition of the existing sewer connections.
	<P><B>Manser Dining Hall:</B>Entech prepared a submission to the Pennsylvania Energy Office for a Technical Assistance Study grant and later conducted a survey of the dining hall. Complete evaluation indicated a potential savings of 30% if all the recomm
endations were implemented.
	<P><B>Memorial Hall - HVAC Rehabilitation: </B>Entech conducted a feasibility study of the two pipe heating and air conditioning system. The study determined the most feasible concept for the rehab of the buildings energy system.  Construction was comple
ted in Sept 1994.
	<P><B>Title V Air Quality Compliance Survey:</B>  Conducted an air emission inventory of nitrogen oxides (NOX), sulfur dioxide, carbon monoxide, particulates, volatile organic compounds (VOCs) and 189 hazardous air pollutants (HAPs).  The purpose of the 
survey was to determine the university's "Potential to Emit" any of these compounds and to determine which PADEP operating permit is applicable to the University.  Entech also prepared the Title V Synthetic Minor Operating Permit Application for the Unive
rsity's submission to the Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection (PADEP).

	<P><B>Miscellaneous Projects: </B>Hemlock Dormitory water leakage investigation; fiber optic distribution system; girls varsity softball field dugouts design;  concrete maintenance program and stormwater runoff collection system. 
	<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A>
	</TD>

