	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
	<HR>
	<P><B>Summer Shutdown: </B> Entech provided design, engineering and construction management for summer shutdown project.  The project included gas fired point of use domestic water heaters in 16 buildings on campus.  Designs used existing steam fired storage tanks for domestic water storage.  Provided steam boiler in cafeteria and installed underground gas lines to three buildings. 

	<P><B>Campus-Wide Energy Audit:</B> Entech  completed a detailed energy study of the entire campus consisting of 33 major buildings totalling 1.5 million square feet of floor area.  The analysis covered all major structural/architectural features relating to heating/cooling and major mechanical-electrical systems on the campus.   Recommended 19 projects estimated to cost $1.2 million which are expected to reduce energy costs by $330,000 or 22%.  Received a construction grant of $100,000 from the Pennsylvania Energy Office.

	<P><B>Campus Master Plan:</B> Developed a campus master plan; project involved:  planning for dormitories, classrooms, gymnasium, administration building, and outdoor track, football and baseball fields.

	<P><B>Architectural Design:</B> Provided architectural design services of Shippen Hall classroom building.

	<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A><P>
