	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
		<HR>
		<B>Waste Management Permit </B>: Entech provided engineering services related to the submission of all necessary Department of Environmental Resources documentation to retain the waste management permit for their existing incineration system.
		<P>
		<P><B>Health Service Campus Boiler Plant</B>: Entech conducted an energy audit for the boiler plant at the Health Services Campus.   The energy evaluation covered all energy systems including outside lighting.  Entech identified the following two (2)  Energy Conservation Opportunities (ECOs):<BR>

<UL>
<LI>Waste Heat Recovery Boiler
<LI>Incandescent to fluorescent lighting retrofit

</UL>

The estimated construction cost for the two ECOs was approximately $70,300.  The estimated annual savings were $24,000 for a 20% reduction from current energy expenditures resulting in a simple payback period of 2.9 years.<P>

Entech also completed and submitted an Energy Conservation Measure (ECM) grant application to the Pennsylvania Energy Office for Cycle XVI funding for the two (2) ECOs.<P>

Contact: Mr. Kurt Bresser, Energy Manager; (215) 787-4515.



