<HEAD>
<TITLE>Villanova University </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ff ff ff" LINK="#FF 00 00 " VLINK="#FF 00 00">
<TABLE WIDTH=591 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR>
	<TD COLSPAN=3 WIDTH=440 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
	<TD WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	<IMG SRC="graphics/150x15.gif" BORDER=0 WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=15>
	</TD>
</TR>	
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=290>
	<H4><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Villanova University
	<BR><IMG SRC="graphics/5x5.gif" BORDER=0>Falvey Hall Library
	</H4>
	</TD>

	<TD  VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=150>
	<BR><TABLE WIDTH=150 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0>
		<TR ALIGN=left>			
			<TD WIDTH=10%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">
			<IMG SRC="graphics/diamond.gif" BORDER=0></A>
			</TD>
			<TD WIDTH=90%>
			<A HREF="../index.html">Main Menu</A>
			</TD>
		</TR>
		</TABLE>
	</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
	<TD WIDTH=50>
	</TD> 

	<TD VALIGN=top ALIGN=left WIDTH=100>
	</TD>

	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
		<HR>
		<B>Falvey Hall </B>:  Entech conducted an energy study of Falvey Hall Library and prepared an Energy Conservation Measure (ECM) grant application for Energy Conservation Opportunities including variable air volume and lighting retrofit projects.<P>

Entech prepared design and bid documents for the retrofit of 1,365; 3' x 3' fluorescent light fixtures utilized for general lighting.  The project included the retrofit of existing 4 lamp T-12 lamps to 3 lamp T-8 lamps and a retrofit of the existing magnetic ballast to new electronic ballast.  U.L. approval was obtained for the retrofit.  <P>

The retrofit project was partially funded by $100,000 ICP Grant from the Pennsylvania Energy Office based upon an Energy Conservation Measure Grant Application prepared by Entech for the University.  This lighting retrofit resulted in a 40% decrease in energy costs for the library.

<P><B>Title V Air Quality Compliance Survey: </B> Conducted an air emissions inventory of nitrogen oxides (NOX), sulfur dioxide, carbon monoxide, particulates, volatile organic compounds (VOCs) and 189 hazardous air pollutants (HAPs).  The purpose of the survey was to determine the University's "Potential to Emit" any of these compounds and to determine which PADEP operating permit is applicable to the University.  Entech also prepared the Title V operating permit application for the University's submission to the Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection (PADEP).

	.<P>

	









		<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A>
	</TD>

</TR>
</TABLE>	
