	<TD COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=middle ALIGN=left WIDTH=440>
		<HR>
		<B>Summer Shutdown </B>:   Entech conducted energy studies and assisted in preparing grant applications for the summer shutdown of the central steam plant and an energy management system.  Grants of $300,000 were awarded.  Also, an energy study was conducted and an Energy Conservation Measure grant application was prepared for a pool dehumidification project.  Entech performed a study for renovating the HVAC system for "New Main."<P>

In 1990, Entech assisted the University in applying for a $100,000 PEO grant for a new pool dehumidification system for the south campus.  This task was completed within a very tight two-week time period.  In 1991, the University was awarded the grant.  Entech has continued to provide technical and economic information to the University for this project which is expected to save almost $100,000 per year in energy costs.<P>

Entech designed renovations to the electrical distribution system under DGS contract 414-55.

  <P><B>Lawrence Hall:</B>

		<P><EM>HVAC Upgrade</EM>. Provided professional engineering/design services to survey and evaluate the operation of HVAC systems and its overall impact on indoor air quality provided to occupants of the building.  Work consisted of evaluating existing operation and performance of the primary HVAC systems serving the dining hall and kitchen facilities, quantify existing air flow volumes of primary air handling equipment, the testing of air quality and the sampling of observed mold and/or mildew in existing ductwork.

		<P><EM>Mechanical Enhancements.</EM> Currently providing engineering/design services for the following enhancements: relocation of kitchen exhaust fans to roof, modify kitchen exhaust away from intakes, installation of kitchen exhaust heat recovery, addition of air handling unit to serve converted locker room, and the evaluation of energy conservation measures.

		<P><A HREF="../college.html">Return to the College list</A>
	</TD>

</TR>
</TABLE>	
<P>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<P>We would be pleased to talk with you about your projects - 
<BR>please contact our VP of Marketing, Matt Lloyd
<BR>at 610-373-6667 or email
<BR><A HREF="mailto:MLloyd@entecheng.novell.net">MLloyd@entecheng.novell.net</A>
