<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Conferences and Workshops</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#8e2323" VLINK="#84590c"><CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/weblogo_small.gif" ALT="The National Arbor Day Foundation" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="40"><BR><IMG SRC="conferences.gif" ALT="Conferences and Workshops" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="89"><BR><HR WIDTH=469><P><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT>The National Arbor Day Foundation is working to help close the gap between what is known and what is practiced in the areas of tree care and environmental stewardship. To meet this goal, the Foundation has developed a wide range of programs to provide opportunities for continuing education and professional development for Foundation members with laymen's interest in trees and the environment and for professionals in government services, the tree care industry and other fields that have a significant impact on trees.<P><B>Upcoming Conferences and Events:</B><P><HR WIDTH=469><P><H2>Trees, People, and the Law</H2><P><I>October 6-8, 1996, Arbor Day Farm's Lied Conference Center, Nebraska City, NE</I><P>$345 with early registration, $395 after September 23.<P>Municipalities, utility companies and private landowners often find themselves involved in litigation resulting from incidents relating to trees. This conference focuses on the rights, duties and liabilities that these entities have with regard to trees and is designed to provide general information on a variety of legal topics, including how the law works, trends in the law, case law, statutory and common law, liability issues and hazard trees.<P><HR WIDTH=469><P><H2>Building with Trees:<BR>Saving Trees at Construction Sites</H2><P><I>September 10, 1996, Newark, NJ<BR>September 17, 1996, Dallas, TX<BR>November 1, 1996, Tulsa, OK<BR>January 14, 1997, St. Louis, MO<BR>January 17, 1997, Springfield, MO</I><P>$125 with early registration, $150 if registration is within 14 days prior to the workshop.<P>Designed primarily for developers, planners, construction managers, builders, real estate staff, urban foresters, arborists, landscapers and other professionals, this one-day, no-nonsense workshop would also benefit citizen leaders, property owners and others with an interest in the preservation of existing trees during construction. This practical workshop can make a difference in your community! It focuses on systematic processes and proven techniques that can turn good intentions into good practices, giving trees a chance to co-exist with development. Also available Chatauqua style.<P><HR WIDTH=469><P><H2>Trees and Utilities National Conference</H2><P><I>February 3-5, 1997, Arbor Day Farm's Lied Conference Center, Nebraska City, NE</I><P>$295 with early registration, $350 after January 20.<P>The third annual conference will be held February 5-7, 1996, at Arbor Day Farm's Lied Conference Center in Nebraska City. This event provides an excellent opportunity for utility professionals,. community foresters and concerned citizens to exchange ideas and explore ways to work together to accomplish the dual goal of growing healthy community forests and providing reliable, low-cost utility service. A key part of the conference will be presentations by a variety of speakers from diverse fields.<P><HR WIDTH=469><P><H2>Shigo on Trees</H2><P><I>March 12, 1997, Austin, TX<BR>March 14, 1997, Indianapolis, IN</I><P>$125 with early registration, $150 if registration is within 14 days prior to the workshop.<P>This popular workshop is conducted by Dr. Alex Shigo, one of the most influential researchers and teachers in the world of tree care.  By synthesizing information from professional journals, the work of other leading scientists and his own research, Dr. Shigo will let you in on the latest theories and discoveries about trees and tree care.  Whether you are new to arboriculture, or are an experienced pro, this will be an unforgettable educational experience.<P><HR WIDTH=469><P><H2>Trees for the World</H2><P><I>June, 1997, Arbor Day Farm's Lied Conference Center, Nebraska City, NE</I><P>By Invitation<P>This conference is designed to be a practical and operation-oriented gathering of organizations from throughout the world that plant trees or fund tree planting. Sponsored by The National Arbor Day Foundation, Jewish National Fund of America and USDA Forest Service -- International Forestry, the conference will provide opportunities to learn about worldwide tree planting projects and programs, to create linkages and global networks for tree planting, and to develop on-going programs to advance tree planting throughout the world.<P><HR WIDTH=469><P><H2>Discovery Workshop: How to Teach Youth About Trees and Environmental Stewardship</H2><P><I>July 24-26, 1997, Arbor Day Farm's Lied Conference Center, Nebraska City, NE</I><P>$295 with early registration, $350 after July 10.<P>This three-day workshop is for anyone who is interested in teaching young people about environmental issues in an interesting, hands-on way. Topics will include tree identification, renewable energy, bio-diversity, food webs, habitat and recycling. Participants will receive a variety of top-notch, kid-tested environmental education materials and learn how to adapt them to meet specific needs.<P><HR><P>If your browser supports secure transactions and you have a credit card...<P><H3><A HREF="https://www.inacomlnk.com/secure/clients/arborday/conference_electronic.html">Click Here for a Secure Electronic Registration Form</A></H3><P><HR><P>If your browser does not support secure transactions or <BR>you want to send a check, money order or purchase order...<P><H3><A HREF="./conference_print.html">Click Here for a Print Registration Form</A></H3><P><HR><P>Or for more information please mail your request to:<P>Conferences <BR>The National Arbor Day Foundation<BR>100 Arbor Avenue<BR>Nebraska City, NE  68410</TABLE><P><HR WIDTH=469><P><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="../join/free_trees.html"><IMG SRC="../images/free_trees_button.gif" ALT="Get 10 Free Trees!" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="../index.html"><IMG SRC="../images/homepage_button.gif" ALT="Return to Homepage" BORDER="0" WIDTH="70" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF="../join/rainforest.html"><IMG SRC="../images/rainforest_button.gif" ALT="Help Rescue the Rainforest!" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD></TABLE></CENTER> </BODY></HTML>
