<HTML>

<HEAD><TITLE>Booklets, Flyers and Newsletters</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#8e2323" VLINK="#84590c">

<CENTER>

<IMG SRC="../images/weblogo_small.gif" ALT="The National Arbor Day Foundation" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="40"><BR>

<IMG SRC="./images/booklets_etc.gif" ALT="Booklets, Flyers and Newsletters" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT= "89"><P>

<A NAME="conservation"><HR WIDTH=469></A><P>

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0>

<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="./images/flyer_conservation.gif" ALT="Conservation Trees"><P></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H2>Conservation Trees for Your Farm, Family, and Future Booklet</H2> This booklet has been prepared to show America's farmers, ranchers, and landowners how to plant and care for conservation trees.  It details the benefits of riparian trees and the elements of a filter strip.  Planting and managing trees for wildlife is introduced through a series of pictures and simple instructions.<P>

<B>Item # 1403 (FREE!)</B><P>
&#128; <A HREF="./ed_order_print.html">Go to Print-Out Order Form</A><P></TD></TR>

<TR><TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><A NAME="america"><HR></A><P>
</TD><TR>

<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="./images/flyer_america.gif" ALT="Trees for America"><P></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H2>Trees for America Brochure</H2> This brochure is an excellent handout for the public at Arbor Day celebrations, wildlife festivals, or tree-planting ceremonies.  It stresses the importance of trees in our communities and each individual's responsiblity in planting and caring for tree, and also contains illustrated tree-planting instructions, information about Arbor Day, a graphic example of the importance of trees to our world, and a coupon for 10 free trees with a membership contribution.<P>

Available individually or in multiples of 50 or 4,000.<P>

<B>Item # 1306 (FREE!)</B><P>
&#128; <A HREF="./ed_order_print.html">Go to Print-Out Order Form</A><P></TD></TR>

<TR><TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><A NAME="rainforest"><HR></A><P>
</TD><TR>

<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="./images/flyer_rainforest.gif" ALT="Rainforest Rescue"><P></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H2>Rain Forest Rescue Flyer</H2> Focuses on the vital importance of the world's rain forests, the threats that they face, and what individuals can do about it.<P>

<B>Item # 1907 (FREE!)</B><P>
&#128; <A HREF="./ed_order_print.html">Go to Print-Out Order Form</A><P></TD></TR>

<TR><TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><A NAME="key"><HR></A><P>
</TD><TR>

<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="./images/tree_key.gif" ALT="What Tree is That?"><P></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H2>&quot;What Tree is That?&quot; Booklet</H2> A pocket-sized tree identification booklet which provides the opportunity for users to identify many of the popular trees in the United States.  This booklet is specifically designed to be used with the <A HREF="./curriculum_kits.html#terrific">Trees are Terrific!</A> curriculum kit.  They use observation and classification skills to guide the user from general leaf characteristics to a specific tree's name.  One version is available for use east of the Rocky Mountains and another for trees west of the Rockies.<P>

Eastern/Central United States version, shipped in packages of 35<BR>
<B>Item # 1195 ($15.40)</B><P>

Western United States version, shipped in packages of 35<BR>
<B>Item # 2446 ($15.40)</B><P>
&#128; <A HREF="https://www.inacomlnk.com/secure/clients/arborday/ed_order_electronic.html">Go to Secure Electronic Order Form</A><BR>
&#128; <A HREF="./ed_order_print.html">Go to Print-Out Order Form</A><P></TD></TR>

<TR><TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><A NAME="junior"><HR></A><P>
</TD><TR>

<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="./images/newsletter_junior.gif" ALT="Junior Steward Newsletter"><P></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H2>Junior Steward Newsletter</H2> A newsletter for young people who are interested in the rain forests and the environmental issues related to them<P>

<B>Item # 2526 (FREE!)</B><P>
&#128; <A HREF="./ed_order_print.html">Go to Print-Out Order Form</A><P></TD></TR>

<TR><TD COLSPAN=2 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><A NAME="carly"><HR></A><P>
</TD><TR>

<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="./images/newsletter_carly.gif" ALT="Carly Chronicle Newsletter"><P></TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H2>Carly Chronicle Newsletter</H2> A semi-annual newsletter those who use the Foundation's <A HREF="./curriculum_kits.html#grow">Grow Your Own Trees</A>, <A HREF="./curriculum_kits.html#terrific">Trees are Terrific!</A> and <A HREF="./curriculum_kits.html#discovery">Discovery Curriculum</A> materials.  Editions contain new ideas, activities and teaching strategies that can be used to teach environmental education concepts.<P>

<B>Item # 1885 (FREE!)</B><P>
&#128; <A HREF="./ed_order_print.html">Go to Print-Out Order Form</A><P></TD></TR>

</TABLE>

