<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>1996 J. Sterling Morton Award</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#8e2323" VLINK="#84590c"><CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/weblogo_small.gif" ALT="The National Arbor Day Foundation" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="40"><IMG SRC="./awards.gif" ALT="1996 Arbor Day Awards" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="89"><P><HR WIDTH=469><P><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="./blank.gif" BORDER="0"></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H2>THE J. STERLING MORTON AWARD</H2><P><HR><P><H3>Dr. Roger C. Funk, Kent, Ohio</H3><P>To know the power of an idea and to foster its adoption is the essence of leadership. It is the central to the observance Arbor Day itself and to the work of J. Sterling Morton, the holiday's founder.<P>The 1996 J. Sterling Morton Award winner carries on that tradition.  He developed the concept of Plant Health Care or PHC.  It is a powerful idea whose time has come.  A holistic approach to plant care, PHC focuses on plant health and growth.  Use of the concept begins with proper soil preparation and proper plant selection.  It goes on to require preventive care and incorporates pest management.  Importantly, pest management is used only when damage warrants, and any control methods selected are those that are the most environmentally friendly.  Under his essential national leadership, the idea has taken strong root throughout the arboricultural profession.<P>He is nationally recognized as a leading authority in the field of tree, lawn and landscape care. He serves on the Biological Pest Control Advisory Panel for the Office of Technology Assessment in Washington, D.C. He holds a doctorate in plant physiology, a master of science in ornamental horticulture and a bachelor of science degree in agriculture from West Virginia University. His responsibilities embrace arboricultural and horticultural consulting, research and development, and training.<P>As Vice President of Human and Technical Resources for The Davey Tree Expert Company, he is affiliated with one of America's preeminent landscape care firms.  During his 20 years with the company he has developed and patented improved fertilizers and pesticide metering systems, and designed its lawn care program.   His research interests include soils, fertilization, and pesticide reduction. It was at Davey that he developed Plant Health Care.<P>He has been a featured speaker for the National Arborist Association, the International Society of Arboriculture, and National Urban Forest Conference, as well as the National Arbor Day Foundation's Tree City USA National Conference and the Trees and Utilities National conference.<P>The American Society for Horticultural Science, the American Institute of Biological Sciences, the International Society for Horticultural Science, the International Society of Arboriculture, the New York Academy of Sciences, the Ohio Academy of Sciences, the Ohio Turfgrass Foundation, the Professional Lawn Care Association of America and the Southern Turfgrass Foundation all count him among their esteemed members.<P>For the energy, enthusiasm, and impact of his work, the National Arbor Day foundation presents its 1996 J. Sterling Morton award to Roger C. Funk of Kent Ohio.<P></TD></TR></TABLE><HR WIDTH=469><P><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="../../join/free_trees.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/free_trees_button.gif" ALT="Get 10 Free Trees!" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/homepage_button.gif" ALT="Return to Homepage" BORDER="0" WIDTH="70" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF="../../join/rainforest.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/rainforest_button.gif" ALT="Join Rain Forest Rescue" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
