<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>1996 Frederick Law Olmsted Award</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#8e2323" VLINK="#84590c"><CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/weblogo_small.gif" ALT="The National Arbor Day Foundation" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="40"><IMG SRC="./awards.gif" ALT="1996 Arbor Day Awards" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="89"><P><HR WIDTH=469><P><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="./blank.gif" BORDER="0"></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H2>THE FREDERICK LAW OLMSTED AWARD</H2><P><HR><P><H3>Deen Day Smith, Norcross, Georgia</H3><P>She gives generously of her time, talent, and resources to awaken citizens of all levels to opportunities and responsibilities to protect and preserve America's natural and man-made beauty.<P>Her vision, leadership, and dedication continually benefit humankind through her sincere commitment to excellence.<P>She has been a driving force in the planting of, protection of and conservation of trees throughout her home state.<P>A graduate and Distinguished Honorary Alumna of Georgia State University, she also holds an Honorary Doctor of Laws degree from Mercer University, is an Honorary Alumna of Georgia Institute of Technology and was the first woman selected to serve on the Board of Directors of the Georgia Chamber of Commerce.<P>She has  received many awards, among them, the Horatio Alger Award; Daughters of the American Revolution Honor Award; The Community Service Board of Governor's Award; The Kiwanis Club International; the Citizen of the Year Award; The Atlanta Panhellenic Association, Outstanding Woman of the Year; and was elected to the Academy of Women Achievers.<P>	Wishing to encourage continuing education for those responsible for the beautification of her city, she has sponsored its Park Employees Beatification Incentive Program which rewards  creativity and resourcefulness in improving parks with erosion control and planting projects.<P>She has distinguished herself, as a leader in the National Garden Club Organization, noted speaker, an active member of environmental, cultural, and philanthropic organizations.<P>She is an inspiration to all who work toward wise stewardship.  She brings a marvelous sense for natural beauty.  She encourages everyone within her wide sphere to work together, donate funds, and seek permanent solutions benefiting  environmental quality.  She fortifies her local, state, and national communities with guidance which insures the success of the many projects she personally underwrites.<P>Lady Bird Johnson wrote of her that, "her enthusiasm, knowledge, pragmatism, her great generosity and good heart are planted deep within the environmental 'vineyard'.  She has inspired others to share her love and concern for this living world of our's, and I have been a witness to her leadership both in her home state and in my personal project, The National Wildflower Research Center.<P>I would describe her as a strong activist and advocate.  She is both a leader and a roll-up-your-sleeves, get-the-job done worker.  I can think of no one more deserving of this signal tribute."<P>For her energy, grace, and inspiration, and for her worthy example, the National Arbor Day Foundation presents its 1996 Frederick Law Olmstead Award to Deen Day Smith of Norcross, Georgia.<P></TD></TR></TABLE><HR WIDTH=469><P><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="../../join/free_trees.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/free_trees_button.gif" ALT="Get 10 Free Trees!" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/homepage_button.gif" ALT="Return to Homepage" BORDER="0" WIDTH="70" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF="../../join/rainforest.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/rainforest_button.gif" ALT="Join Rain Forest Rescue" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
