<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>1996 Lady Bird Johnson Award</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#8e2323" VLINK="#84590c"><CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/weblogo_small.gif" ALT="The National Arbor Day Foundation" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="40"><IMG SRC="./awards.gif" ALT="1996 Arbor Day Awards" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="89"><P><HR WIDTH=469><P><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="./blank.gif" BORDER="0"></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H2>THE LADY BIRD JOHNSON AWARD</H2><P><HR><P><H3>Bull Street Improvement Project, Savannah, Georgia</H3><P>A 1.5 million dollar, privately-funded, 5-year improvement program, the Bull Street Improvement Project is administered by the Historic Savannah Foundation and executed in cooperation with the City of Savannah.<P>Created to restore the spine of Savannah's Historic District to its former glory, the Bull Street Improvement Project is to serve as a model for what can be achieved throughout the area.  Its major goal is to restore the street's tree canopy. During the first year of the project, magnolia, holly trees, live oak, and other evergreens were planted.<P>As much of the impermeable, concrete sidewalk material as possible, was removed and the walks relayed with brick or stone on a base of compacted sand.  This element of the project is important so that air and water can penetrate and nourish the roots of the young trees, while also improving conditions for older, existing, mature trees.  To further enhance the new corridor, tree lawns have been planted with Asian jasmine as a ground cover.<P>New period lighting, litter bins, street name and traffic signs have also been installed.<P>Now in its fourth year, the project will be completing the fifth and final phase in May of 1996.<P>The Bull Street Improvement Project has inspired a renewed enthusiasm and respect for the heritage of Savannah's historic landscapes, both natural and built.<P>For its vision of graceful green, growing to bring beauty to heritage, the National Arbor Day Foundation presents its 1996 Lady Bird Johnson Award to The Bull Street Improvement Project of Savannah, Georgia.<P></TD></TR></TABLE><HR WIDTH=469><P><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="../../join/free_trees.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/free_trees_button.gif" ALT="Get 10 Free Trees!" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/homepage_button.gif" ALT="Return to Homepage" BORDER="0" WIDTH="70" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF="../../join/rainforest.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/rainforest_button.gif" ALT="Join Rain Forest Rescue" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
