<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Celebrate Arbor Day!</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#8e2323" VLINK="#84590c"><CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/weblogo_small.gif" ALT="The National Arbor Day Foundation" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="40"><BR><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=10><TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP><IMG SRC="images/celebrate.gif" ALT="Celebrate Arbor Day!" WIDTH="195" HEIGHT="120"></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>National Arbor Day is the last Friday in April, although many states celebrate at other times. (Our free <I>Trees for America</I> flyer lists each date.) Arbor Day celebrations emphasize that tree planting is a personal demonstration of stewardship. Continuing a tradition begun in 1872 by J. Sterling Morton, the Foundation recognizes the good stewards of today and educates the good stewards of tomorrow.<P>For more information about Arbor Day and to get ideas for your celebration, write for our free <I>Celebrate Arbor Day!</I> booklet. Mail your request to: <P>The National Arbor Day Foundation<BR>100 Arbor Avenue<BR>Nebraska City, NE 68410<P></TD></TR></TABLE><P><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="../../join/free_trees.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/free_trees_button.gif" ALT="Get 10 Free Trees!" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/homepage_button.gif" ALT="Return to Homepage" BORDER="0" WIDTH="70" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF="../../join/rainforest.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/rainforest_button.gif" ALT="Help Rescue the Rainforest!" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
