<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Lied Conference Center</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#8e2323" VLINK="#84590c"><CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/weblogo_small.gif" ALT="The National Arbor Day Foundation" WIDTH="469" HEIGHT="40"><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TD ALIGN=LEFT COLSPAN=3><FONT SIZE=+4><B>Lied Conference Center</B></FONT><BR><HR><P></TD></TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT><IMG SRC="./images/lied_center.gif" WIDTH="200"><P></TD><TD><PRE> </PRE><P></TD><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>Lied Conference Center (pronounced <I>lead</I> as in leadership) is the only education center of its kind in America with staff and programs dedicated to tree planting and environmental stewardship.<BR>In addition to environmental conferences and annual Arbor Day Farm activities, Lied Conference Center is open to the public for meetings, weekend getaways, or dining in the restaurant.</TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=3 ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP><H3>The Perfect Site for Conferences and Training</H3>Located only 50 minutes from the Omaha, Nebraska airport, Lied Conference Center offers a superb environment for any meeting or conference. Special low rates are available for conservation-related conferences and events.<P>The National Arbor Day Foundation regularly convenes conferences at Lied Conference Center to find creative solutions for the complex problems facing trees and the environment. It is the Foundation's goal for Arbor Day Farm to become a nationally and internationally recognized forum for discussions of sustainability.<P>For more information on currently scheduled Foundation conferences, see our page on <A HREF="../../conferences/conferences.html">Conferences and Workshops</A>.<P><H3>An Environmentally Friendly Building</H3>Lied Conference Center is designed to demonstrate numerous state-of-the-art environmentally friendly construction features. The building's conservation checklist includes:<BR><LI>Wood windows (with argon-filled, double coated, low-E, insulated glass) and French doors, a gift of Pella Corporation, of Pella, Iowa. <LI>Compact-flourescent light fixtures, with bulbs contributed by Philips Lighting Company.<LI>Heating and cooling with renewable fuelwood. (See page on <A HREF="fuelwood_plant.html">Fuelwood Plant</A>.)<LI>No CFCs used for air conditioning.<LI>Comprehensive recycling systems.<LI>Water-conserving plumbing fixtures.<LI>Lodging-room carpet made from recycled pop bottles. <LI>Clean-burning, energy-efficient fireplaces.<P>For more information call Lied Conference Center at 1-800-546-5433 <B>or</B> visit the <A HREF="http://www.adflcc.com">Lied Conference Center web site</A>.<P></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=3><HR><P></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=469 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="../../join/free_trees.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/free_trees_button.gif" ALT="Get 10 Free Trees!" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/homepage_button.gif" ALT="Return to Homepage" BORDER="0" WIDTH="70" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF="../../join/rainforest.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/rainforest_button.gif" ALT="Help Rescue the Rainforest!" BORDER="0" WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="40"></A></TD></TABLE></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
