<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>What's New on the PCMDI Web?</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.01Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bg9.gif">

<P><B><FONT SIZE=+2>What's New on the PCMDI Web?</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+2>
</FONT>
<HR></P>

<P>The following are recent additions to PCMDI's Web pages: </P>

<UL>
<LI>The PCMDI Web is now <A HREF="http://www.bom.gov.au/bmrc/clch/pcmdi-mirror/index.html">mirrored
in Australia</A>, courtesy of the Bureau of Meteorology Research Centre
(<A HREF="http://www.bom.gov.au/bmrc">BMRC</A>) (February 6, 1997). <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI>Version 2.7 of the Visualization and Computation System (VCS) software
and related documentation may be accessed from the <A HREF="../williams/vcs/vcshome.html">VCS
home page</A> (January 30, 1997) <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI>Retrieval of data stored in a variety of popular formats (netCDF, GrADS,
GRIB, DRS) is facilitated by PCMDI's <A HREF="../ktaylor/ezget/ezget.html">EzGet
Fortran Library</A> which can be downloaded from our Web (December 26,
1996). <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI><A HREF="../zhang/report38/rep38.htm">PCMDI Report No. 38</A> on &quot;Climatology
of East Asian winter monsoon and cold surges: Results from the 1979-1995
NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis&quot; by Yi Zhang et al. is published (November 25,
1996) <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI>Information on the Coupled Model Intercomparison Project (CMIP) and
CMIP I/CMIP II intercomparison experiments is accessible from the <A HREF="../covey/cmip/cmiphome.html">CMIP
home page</A> (November 20, 1996) <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI>Version 1.3 of the <A HREF="modldoc/amip/amip.html">Summary Documentation
of the AMIP Models</A> is released. Among other <A HREF="modldoc/amip/01new.html">innovations</A>,
information is provided on 16 new models (November 15, 1996) <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI>PCMDI staff member Mike Fiorino is providing convenient access to daily
<A HREF="http://www-pcmdi.llnl.gov/fiorino/wxmap/wx.htm">numerical weather
prediction (NWP) maps</A> for North America, Europe, and Asia. The maps
are generated by two NWP institutions: the National Centers for Envivornmental
Prediction (<A HREF="http://www.ncep.noaa.gov">NCEP</A>) and the U.S. Navy's
Fleet Numerical Meteorology and Oceanography Center (<A HREF="http://www.fnoc.navy.mil">FNMOC</A>)
(November 5, 1996). <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI>PCMDI Report No. 36 &quot;On the Maintenance and Initiation of the
Intraseasonal Oscillation in the NCEP/NCAR Reanalysis and the GLA and UKMO
AMIP Simulations&quot; by K. Sperber et al. <A HREF="../sperber/report36/Rpt36.htm">is
published</A> (November 5, 1996). <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI>The next phase of the Atmospheric Model Intercomparison Project, designated
as <A HREF="../amip2/overview.html">AMIP II</A>, is launched. Guidelines
for AMIP II are published in <A HREF="../amip2/amipnl8.html">AMIP Newsletter
No. 8</A>. There also are frequent additions and/or updates of <A HREF="../amiphome.html">other
AMIP II documents</A> (November 5, 1996). <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI>The <A HREF="../susan/amiphistory.html">AMIP history data status</A>
is updated (September 4, 1996). <BR>
<BR>
</LI>

<LI>Our list of <A HREF="climategrps.html">Related WWW Groups</A> also
is updated frequently. </LI>
</UL>

<P>
<HR><A HREF="../PCMDI.html">Return to PCMDI home page</A> 
<HR><BR>
Last update February 16, 1997. For questions or comments, contact<BR>
Tom Phillips(<A HREF="mailto:phillips@tworks.llnl.gov&quot;">phillips@tworks.llnl.gov</A>)
</P>

