<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Public Data Archives</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.01Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bg9.gif">

<P><B><FONT SIZE=+2>Public Data Archives</FONT></B> <IMG SRC="network8.gif" HEIGHT=54 WIDTH=64>
<HR></P>

<P>Public data presently archived at PCMDI include the monthly mean <A HREF="../gleckler/amipso.html">standard
output data</A> generated by 30 different <A HREF="AMIPorigroups.html">atmospheric
models</A>. <I>Contact Peter Gleckler (<A HREF="mailto:gleckler@pcmdi.llnl.gov">gleckler@pcmdi.llnl.gov</A>)
for ftp access instructions, and include a brief summary of the intended
use of the data so that we can refer you to others doing similar studies.</I>(See
also information on the <A HREF="AMIPsubprojects.html">AMIP diagnostic
subprojects</A>.) </P>

<P>Access to high-frequency <A HREF="../susan/amiphistory.html">history
data</A> from some dozen AMIP models is also possible, provided that a
brief research proposal is approved by the <A HREF="../mccravy/amipnl7.html#AMIP Panel">AMIP
panel</A>. <I>Before composing a proposal, contact Peter Gleckler (<A HREF="mailto:gleckler@pcmdi.llnl.gov">gleckler@pcmdi.llnl.gov</A>)
for instructions on its expected format, and for further details on available
history data (which differ across the models)</I>. </P>

<P>In the future, we plan to make both public model-based and observational
data available for downloading directly from the PCMDI Web. </P>

<P>
<HR><A HREF="../PCMDI.html">Return to PCMDI home page</A> 
<HR><BR>
Last update February 16, 1997. For questions concerning AMIP model data,
contact Peter Gleckler (<A HREF="mailto:gleckler@pcmdi.llnl.gov">gleckler@pcmdi.llnl.gov</A>).<BR>
This page is maintained by <A HREF="mailto:mccravy@pcmdi.llnl.gov">mccravy@pcmdi.llnl.gov
<HR WIDTH="100%"><A HREF="http://www.llnl.gov"><IMG SRC="lll.gif" HEIGHT=32 WIDTH=32></A></A>&nbsp;and
<A HREF="http://www.llnl.gov/disclaimer.html">LLNL Disclaimers</A> </P>

<P>UCRL-MI-119847 </P>

</BODY>
</HTML>
