<html>
<head><title>The PCMDI Mission</title></head>
<body background="blue_paper.gif">
<h1>The PCMDI Mission</h1>
<hr>
<p>
<p>
 PCMDI's principal mission is to develop improved methods and tools for the diagnosis,validation and intercomparison of global climate models--what we call <A HREF="infrastr.html"><I>climate modeling infrastructure</I></A>. 
<P>
The need for standards in both modeling and analysis has become increasingly
apparent as more complex models are developed, while the disagreement
among models, and between models and observations, remains significant and poorly understood.  The nature and causes of these disagreements must be accounted for in a systematic fashion before models can be confidently used for climate sensitivity and predictability studies in support of global change research.
<p>
Complementing these goals, PCMDI scientists also engage in <A HREF="PCMDIresearch.html">research</A> on a wide variety of outstanding problems in climate modeling and analysis, and <A HREF="PCMDIpubs.html">publish</A> results of these investigations in a variety of forums.
<P><BR>
<hr>
<a href=../PCMDItoc.html>Return to PCMDI directory</a>
<br>
