<html>
<head><title>Model Validation</title></head>
<body background="blue_paper.gif">
<h1>Model Validation</h1>
<hr>
<p>
Because validation is central to the diagnosis and intercomparison of global climate models, PCMDI is developing observational data products as an essential element of a <A HREF="infrastr.html">climate modeling infrastructure</A>.  
<P>
Our current priority is to accumulate observational data (including reanalyses) from the AMIP period of 1979-1988, but a longer-term goal is to acquire quality datasets that are generally useful for climate model validation. In the future, we plan to disseminate much of our validation data over the World Wide Web.
<P>
Statistical and dynamical analysis tools for the systematic  and comprehensive validation of global climate models are also under development at PCMDI. It is intended that these diagnostics will eventually be integrated into a single software library and disseminated to the <A HREF="climategrps.html">world climate community</A>.    

<p>
<hr>
<a href=../PCMDItoc.html>Return to PCMDI directory</a>
<br>
<hr>
<br>
Last update September 9, 1996.  For questions, contact<br>
Mike Fiorino (<a href="mailto:fiorino@pcmdi.llnl.gov">fiorino@pcmdi.llnl.gov</a>)
<p>
<a href="http://www.llnl.gov/disclaimer.html">LLNL Disclaimers</a>
