<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>PCMDI Software Tools</TITLE>
   
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bg9.gif">

<P><FONT SIZE=+2>An Overview of PCMDI Software Tools</FONT>
<HR></P>

<P>An important component of PCMDI's work is the development, testing,
and distribution of software tools for the storage, diagnosis, and visualization
of data. </P>

<P>These include tools for data I/O management (historically <A HREF="../drach/DRS.html">DRS</A>--now
superceded by <A HREF="../drach/cdunif.html">cdunif,&nbsp;</A><A HREF="../ktaylor/ezget/ezget.html">EzGet</A>,
and <A HREF="../amip2/lats/latstemp.html">LATS</A>); tools for data visualization
and computation (<A HREF="../williams/vcs/vcshome.html">VCS</A>); and tools
for the translation of data for different formats and visualization platforms
(<A HREF="../williams/ddi/ddi.html">DDI</A>). </P>

<P>A comprehensive climate database management system (CDMS) also is currently
under development at PCMDI. This tool will provide efficient access of
information from both our model and observational data archives. </P>

<P>Presently, all PCMDI software products are freely available as binaries.
Source codes for some products are not generally available, but may be
distributed to PCMDI collaborators. Check the <A HREF="../Softwaretoc.html">information
on each product</A> for specifics. </P>

<P><BR>

<HR><A HREF="../Softwaretoc.html">Return to Software Tools Directory</A>

<HR><BR>
Last update February 6, 1997. For questions on PCMDI software products,
contact Dean Williams (<A HREF="mailto: williams@pcmdi.llnl.gov">williams@pcmdi.llnl.gov</A>)
<HR WIDTH="100%"><A HREF="http://www.llnl.gov/"><IMG SRC="lll.gif" HEIGHT=32 WIDTH=32></A>&nbsp;and
<A HREF="http://www.llnl.gov/disclaimer.html">LLNL Disclaimers</A></P>

