<head><title>AMIP Studies</title></head>
<body background="blue_paper.gif">
<h1>AMIP Studies</h1>
<hr>
<p>
PCMDI scientists are diagnosing different aspects of <a href=../phillips/modldoc/amip/amip.html> AMIP model</a> simulations, both independently and in association with <a href=../phillips/AMIPsubprojects.html>AMIP diagnostic subprojects</a>.  This work is summarized in the following publications.

<p>
<br>
<b>References</b>
<p>
Boyle, J.S., 1993:  Preliminary validation of the low frequency variability of tropospheric temperature and circulation simulated for the AMIP by the ECMWF model.  PCMDI Report No. 11, 20 pp.<A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP11">Abstract</A>
<p>
Boyle, J.S., 1994:  The northern wintertime divergence extrema at 200 hPa and surface cyclones as simulated in the AMIP integration of the ECMWF general circulation model.  PCMDI Report No. 20, 27 pp.<A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP20">Abstract</A>
<p>
Boyle, J. S., 1994:  The northern wintertime divergence extrema at 200 hPa and
MSLP cyclones as simulated in the AMIP integration by the ECMWF general
circulation model.  <i>Journal of Climate</i>, <b>7</b>, 24-32. 
<p>
Boyle, J. S., 1994:  Low frequency variability in AMIP model monthly mean data
for the Northern winter for the 200 hPa streamfunction.  <i>Journal of Climate</i>(in press).
<p>
Boyle, J. S., 1994:  The interrelationship between temperature changes in the
free atmosphere (MSU channel 2) and sea surface temperature changes in a ten
year AMIP climate simulation.  <i>Journal of Geophysical Research</i>, <b>99</b>, 10365-10375.
<P>
Boyle, J.S., 1995:  Intercomparison of the spectral characteristics of 200 hPa kinetic energy in AMIP GCM simulations.  PCMDI Report No. 23, 37 pp.<A HREF="../boyle/pubs/Rept23/rpt23h~1.htm">Hypertext</A>
<P>
Boyle, J.S., 1995:  Estimates of zonally averaged tropical diabatic heating in AMIP GCM simulations.  PCMDI Report No. 25, 35 pp.<A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP25">Abstract</A>
<P>
Boyle, J.S., 1996: Seasonal characteristics of precipitation over the United States in AMIP simulations.  PCMDI Report No. 31, 30 pp. <A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP31">Abstract</A>
<P>
Boyle, J.S., 1996: Intercomparison of low-frequency variability of the global 200 hPa circulation for AMIP simulations.  PCMDI Report No. 32, 48 pp.<A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP32">Abstract</A>
<P>
Boyle, J.S., 1996: Intercomparison of the seasonal cycle in 200 hPa kinetic energy in AMIP GCM simulations.  PCMDI Report No. 37, 34 pp.

<P>
Covey, C., 1996:  Correlation between outgoing longwave radiation and surface temperature in the Tropical Pacific:  A model intercomparison.  PCMDI Report No. 30, 10 pp.  <A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP30">Abstract</A>
<P>
Gleckler, P.J., D.A. Randall, G. Boer, R. Colman, M. Dix, V. Galin, M. Helfand, J. Kiehl, A. Kitoh, W. Lau, X.-Z. Liang, V. Lykossov, B. McAvaney, K. Miyakoda, and S. Planton, 1994:  Cloud-radiative effects on implied oceanic energy transports as simulated by atmospheric general circulation models.  PCMDI Report No. 15, 13 pp.<A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP15">Abstract</A>
<p>
Gleckler, P.J., D.A. Randall, G. Boer, R. Colman, M. Dix, V. Galin, M. Helfand, J. Kiehl, A. Kitoh, W. Lau, X.-Z. Liang, V. Lykossov, B. McAvaney, K. Miyakoda, S. Planton, and W. Stern, 1995:  Cloud-radiative effects on implied oceanic energy transports as simulated by atmospheric general circulation models.  <i>Geophysical Research Letters</i>, <b>22</b>, 791-794.
<p>
Palmer, T.N., D. Battisti, C. Brankovic, R. Buizza, Y.-Q. Chen, and K. Sperber, 1995:  Ensemble techniques for seasonal prediction.  In Proceedings of the 1995 Tropical and Ocean-Global Atmosphere (TOGA) Conference, Melbourne, Australia, April 2-7, 1995.
 <P>
Sengupta, S.K., and J.S. Boyle, 1993:  Statistical intercomparison of global climate models:  A common principal component approach.  PCMDI Report No. 13, 41 pp.<A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP13">Abstract</A>
<P>
Sengupta, S.K., and J.S. Boyle, 1995:  Nonlinear principal component analysis of climate data.  PCMDI Report No. 29, 21 pp.<A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP29">Abstract</A>
<p>
Slingo, J. M.,  K.R. Sperber, J.S.Boyle, J.-P. Ceron, M. Dix, B. Dugas, W. Ebisuzaki, J.Fyfe, D. Gregory,  J.-F. Gueremy, J. Hack, A. Harzallah, P. Inness,  A. Kitoh, W. K.-M. Lau, B. McAvaney, R. Madden, A. Matthews, T. N. Palmer,   C.-K. Park, D. Randall, N. Renno, 1995: Intraseasonal oscillations in 15 general circulation models: Results from an AMIP subproject.  Report WCRP-88, World Climate Research Programme, Geneva, Switzerland.    
<P>
Slingo, J. M.,  K.R. Sperber, J.S.Boyle, J.-P. Ceron, M. Dix, B. Dugas, W. Ebisuzaki, J.Fyfe, D. Gregory,  J.-F. Gueremy, J. Hack, A. Harzallah, P. Inness,  A. Kitoh, W. K.-M. Lau, B. McAvaney, R. Madden, A. Matthews, T. N. Palmer,   C.-K. Park, D. Randall, N. Renno, 1996:  Intraseasonal oscillations in 15 general circulation models: Results from an AMIP subproject.  <I>Climate Dynamics</I>, <B>12</B>, 325-357.
<p>
Sperber, K. R., and T. N. Palmer, 1994: Atmospheric Model Intercomparison Project: Monsoon Simulations. In Proceedings of the International Conference on Monsoon Variability and Prediction, Trieste, Italy, May 9-13, 1994. Vol. 2, 601-608.
<p>
Sperber, K. R., and T. N. Palmer, 1994: Monsoons: AMIP simulations of the 1987 and 1988 drought and flood regimes. In Proceedings of the Eighteenth Annual Climate Diagnostics Workshop, Boulder, CO, November 1-5, 1993, 122-125.
<p>
Sperber, K. R., and T. N. Palmer, 1995:  Atmospheric Model Intercomparison Project:  Variability and extreme events.  Submitted to the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change: Scientific Assessment of Climate Change.
<P>
 Sperber, K. R., and T. N. Palmer, 1995:  Interannual tropical rainfall variability in general circulation model simulations associated with the Atmospheric Model Intercomparison Project.  PCMDI Report No. 28 (also <i>Journal of Climate</i>, in press), 79 pp.<A HREF="PCMDIreports.html#RP28">Abstract</A>
<P>
