<html><head><title>ECMWF Model AMIP Simulations</head></title>
<body background="blue_paper.gif">
<body>
<H1>ECMWF Model AMIP Simulations</H1>
<hr>
<p>
The following realizations of the <a href="../amiphome.html">AMIP</a> experiment were conducted with the cycle 36 version of the ECMWF model.  For further information, see the <a href="../phillips/modldoc/amip/19ecm_ToC.html">summary documentation</a> of this model's features.
<p>
<br>
<PRE>
<b>Experiment number:    EC9104</b>

Description:          ECMWF T42L19 AMIP 10 Year Simulation ( 1979-1988 ).
                      This is the original ECMWF AMIP simulation run with the
                      cycle 36 version of the model.

Initial conditions:   ECMWF analysis of January 15 1979 00 GMT

Simulation t=0:       January 1, 1979 00 GMT

Boundary conditions:  Sea Surface Temperatures and sea-ice distribution are
                      from the official AMIP ten year dataset of monthly means.
                      Other boundary conditions specifying albedo, surface 
                      roughness, vegetation type, etc are from the ECMWF
                      climatology.

Output intervals:     Radiative fluxes are available every three hours.
                      History of state is output every six hours
                      Accumulated history is output once daily.

Peculiarities:        No runoff output.  Three dimensional cloudiness could not
                      be recovered from the history of state.  Some errors
                      present in setting sea-ice near sea-ice boundaries after
                      year one of the integration.


<b>Experiment number:    EC9201</b>

Description:          ECMWF T42L19 AMIP 10 Year Simulation ( 1979-1988 ).
                      This is the First Repeat of the ECMWF AMIP simulation
                      run with the cycle 36 version of the model.

Initial conditions:   Taken from the end of the original ECMWF AMIP simulation,
                      EC9104.

Simulation t=0:       January 1, 1979 00 GMT

Boundary conditions:  Sea Surface Temperatures and sea-ice distribution are
                      from the official AMIP ten year dataset of monthly means.
                      Other boundary conditions specifying albedo, surface 
                      roughness, vegetation type, etc are from the ECMWF
                      climatology.

Output intervals:     Radiative fluxes are available every three hours.
                      History of state is output every six hours
                      Accumulated history is output every six hours.

Peculiarities:        Some errors present in setting sea-ice near sea-ice
                      boundaries after year one of the integration.


<b>Experiment number:    EC9202</b>

Description:          ECMWF T42L19 AMIP 10 Year Simulation ( 1979-1988 ).
                      This is the original Ten Seasonal Cycles of AMIP
                      Climatology run with the cycle 36 version of the model.

Initial conditions:   Taken from the end of the original ECMWF AMIP simulation,
                      EC9104. 

Simulation t=0:       January 1, 1979 00 GMT

Boundary conditions:  Sea Surface Temperatures and sea-ice distribution are
                      from the official AMIP ten year dataset of monthly means.
                      In the special case of this experiment, each of the ten
                      year monthly means for each month are averaged to produce
                      a one year climatology of values which are then used
                      to prescribe sea surface temperature and sea-ice
                      distribution for ten consecutive seasonal cycles.
                      Other boundary conditions specifying albedo, surface
                      roughness, vegetation type, etc are from the ECMWF
                      climatology.

Output intervals:     Radiative fluxes are available every three hours.
                      History of state is output every six hours.
                      Accumulated history is output every six hours.

Peculiarities:        Large errors present in setting sea surface temperatures
                      after year one make this integration un-usable.


<b>Experiment number:    EC9203</b>

Description:          ECMWF T42L19 AMIP 10 Year Simulation ( 1979-1988 ).
                      This is the Second Repeat of the ECMWF AMIP simulation
                      run with the cycle 36 version of the model.

Initial conditions:   Taken from the end of the first repeat of the ECMWF AMIP
                      simulation, EC9201. 

Simulation t=0:       January 1, 1979 00 GMT

Boundary conditions:  Sea Surface Temperatures and sea-ice distribution are
                      from the official AMIP ten year dataset of monthly means.
                      Other boundary conditions specifying albedo, surface
                      roughness, vegetation type, etc are from the ECMWF
                      climatology.

Output intervals:     Radiative fluxes are available every three hours.
                      History of state is output every six hours
                      Accumulated history is output every six hours.

Peculiarities:        Some errors present in setting sea-ice near sea-ice
                      boundaries after year one of the integration.


<b>Experiment number:    EC9204</b>

Description:          ECMWF T42L19 AMIP 10 Year Simulation ( 1979-1988 ).
                      This is the Third Repeat of the ECMWF AMIP simulation
                      run with the cycle 36 version of the model.

Initial conditions:   Taken from the end of the second repeat of the ECMWF AMIP
                      simulation, EC9203.

Simulation t=0:       January 1, 1979 00 GMT

Boundary conditions:  Sea Surface Temperatures and sea-ice distribution are
                      from the official AMIP ten year dataset of monthly means.
                      Other boundary conditions specifying albedo, surface
                      roughness, vegetation type, etc are from the ECMWF
                      climatology.

Output intervals:     Radiative fluxes are available every three hours.
                      History of state is output every six hours
                      Accumulated history is output every six hours.

Peculiarities:        Some errors present in setting sea-ice near sea-ice
                      boundaries after year one of the integration.


<b>Experiment number:    EC9301</b>

Description:          ECMWF T42L19 AMIP 10 Year Simulation ( 1979-1988 ).
                      This is the Fourth Repeat of the ECMWF AMIP simulation
                      run with the cycle 36 version of the model.

Initial conditions:   Taken from the end of the third repeat of the ECMWF AMIP
                      simulation, EC9204.

Simulation t=0:       January 1, 1979 00 GMT

Boundary conditions:  Sea Surface Temperatures and sea-ice distribution are
                      from the official AMIP ten year dataset of monthly means.
                      Other boundary conditions specifying albedo, surface
                      roughness, vegetation type, etc are from the ECMWF
                      climatology.

Output intervals:     Radiative fluxes are available every three hours.
                      History of state is output every six hours
                      Accumulated history is output every six hours.

Peculiarities:        Some errors present in setting sea-ice near sea-ice
                      boundaries after year one of the integration.


<b>Experiment number:    EC9302</b>

Description:          ECMWF T106L19 AMIP 4 Year Simulation ( 1985-1988 ).
                      This is a high resolution (T106) ECMWF AMIP simulation
                      run with the cycle 33 version of the model.  The
                      simulation is for the four years of AMIP 1985-1988.

Initial conditions:   Taken from a January of a previous T106 ECMWF simulation,
                      EC9019.

Simulation t=0:       December 2, 1984 00 GMT

Boundary conditions:  Sea Surface Temperatures and sea-ice distribution are
                      from the official AMIP ten year dataset of monthly means.
                      Other boundary conditions specifying albedo, surface
                      roughness, vegetation type, etc are from the ECMWF
                      climatology.

Output intervals:     Radiative fluxes are available every three hours.
                      History of state is output every six hours
                      Accumulated history is output every six hours.

Peculiarities:        Some errors present in setting sea-ice near sea-ice
                      boundaries after year one of the integration.


<b>Experiment number:    EC9303</b>

Description:          ECMWF T42L19 AMIP 10 Year Simulation ( 1979-1988 ).
                      This is the first repeat of the Ten Seasonal Cycles of
                      AMIP Climatology run with the cycle 36 version of the
                      model.

Initial conditions:   Taken from the end of the first repeat of the ECMWF AMIP
                      simulation, EC9201.

Simulation t=0:       January 1, 1979 00 GMT

Boundary conditions:  Sea Surface Temperatures and sea-ice distribution are
                      from the official AMIP ten year dataset of monthly means.
                      In the special case of this experiment, each of the ten
                      year monthly means for each month are averaged to produce
                      a one year climatology of values which are then used
                      to prescribe sea surface temperature and sea-ice
                      distribution for ten consecutive seasonal cycles.
                      Other boundary conditions specifying albedo, surface
                      roughness, vegetation type, etc are from the ECMWF
                      climatology.

Output intervals:     Radiative fluxes are available every three hours.
                      History of state is output every six hours
                      Accumulated history is output every six hours.

Peculiarities:        Large errors present in setting sea surface temperatures
                      after year one make this integration un-usable.


<b>Experiment number:    EC9304</b>

Description:          ECMWF T106L19 AMIP 4 Year Simulation ( 1985-1988 ).
                      This is a high resolution (T106) ECMWF AMIP simulation
                      run with the cycle 36 version of the model.  The
                      simulation is for the four years of AMIP 1985-1988.

Initial conditions:   Taken from a January of a previous T106 ECMWF simulation,
                      EC9019.

Simulation t=0:       December 2, 1984 00 GMT

Boundary conditions:  Sea Surface Temperatures and sea-ice distribution are
                      from the official AMIP ten year dataset of monthly means.
                      Other boundary conditions specifying albedo, surface
                      roughness, vegetation type, etc are from the ECMWF
                      climatology.

Output intervals:     Radiative fluxes are available every three hours.
                      History of state is output every six hours
                      Accumulated history is output every six hours.

Peculiarities:        Some errors present in setting sea-ice near sea-ice
                      boundaries after year one of the integration.


