<d><title>AMIP II Overview</title></head>
<body background="blue_paper.gif">
<h1>The Next Phase: AMIP II</h1>
<hr>
<p>
<p>
With the endorsement of the Working Group on Numerical Experimentation (WGNE) of the World
Climate Research Programme, the PCMDI has agreed to coordinate the next phase of AMIP.  
The WGNE has appointed seven scientists to serve as members of the international AMIP Panel, who
have assisted PCMDI in the design of AMIP II.  The recommendations
of many AMIP participants also have been incorporated. 
<p>
As in AMIP I, the primary objective of AMIP II will be to support a community standard
control experiment of global atmospheric general circulation models.  <A HREF="http://www-pcmdi.llnl.gov/amip2/proposals.html">
Diagnostic subprojects</a> will be established 
to coordinate comprehensive analyses of the AMIP II simulations.
There will also be a special effort to study the effect of intrinsic
variability on the simulations, and support will be given to some numerical experimentation.
<p>
For further information, refer to the <A HREF="amipnl8.html">AMIP II Guidelines</A> published
in AMIP Newsletter No. 8.  All inquires should be sent to
<a href="mailto: amip@pcmdi.llnl.gov">amip@pcmdi.llnl.gov</a> or to the 
AMIP Project Office, PCMDI, L-264, LLNL, P.O. Box 808, Livermore, CA, 
94550, USA.


<P><BR>
