<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>AMIP II Sea Surface Temperatures</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.01Gold (X11; I; IRIX 5.3 IP22) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EF" VLINK="#52188C" ALINK="#FF0000">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>AMIP II Sea Surface Temperature and Sea Ice: Observational
and Boundary Condition Data Sets</H1>

<P>
<HR>The AMIP II SST and sea ice boundary conditons is available at this
site.<B> </B>Two distinctly different data sets have been prepared. The
first is the AMIP II SST and sea ice <B>observational data set</B>. These
data represent the monthly averages of the SST and sea ice data used in
both the ECMWF and NCEP reanalysis projects, although several important
corrections were made. </P>

<P>The second data set is the AMIP II SST and sea ice <B>boundary conditions</B>.
These data are derived from the observational data set, and is <B>to be
used in the AMIP II simulations</B>. The primary difference between the
boundary condition data set and the observational data set is that adjustments
have been made to insure that when it is linearly interpolated between
monthly average values (i.e., when used as boundary conditions for an AGCM),
<I>the monthly average of the observations is preserved</I>. Monthly averages
are not preserved when the observations are linearly intepolated between
monthly average values (as in AMIP I) because the interpolation process
utilizes three months for each simulated month (e.g., Jan, Feb and Mar
are all used for the Feb values). When the boundary condition data is used
for an AGCM simulation, it has been shown that in addition to preserving
the observational monthly means, the seasonal cycle and the interannual
variance are more accurately represented than the method used in AMIP I.
</P>

<P>Both these data sets have been reviewed by experts in the community.
Documents (soon to be finalized) are available for both data sets: </P>

<LI><A HREF="http://kuala.llnl.gov/amip2/amip2_bcs.htm">AMIP II SST and
Sea ice <B>Observations: </B>documentation (data available soon)</A></LI>

<LI><A HREF="amip2bcs.html">AMIP II SST and Sea ice <B>Boundary Condition:
</B>documentation and data</A></LI>

<P>
<HR><A HREF="../../amiphome.html">Return to AMIP home page</A> <BR>

<HR><BR>
Last update 27 January 1997</P>

<P><A HREF="http://www.llnl.gov/disclaimer.html">LLNL Disclaimers</A> </P>

<P>UCRL-MI-125597 </P>

</BODY>
