<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Conference Center</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR = "#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<img src="images/ccheader.gif"><br>
</center>
<P>
<P>
<BR>

Guided by CCECS' mission of providing lifelong learning opportunities for adults through research, teaching and service, the Conference Center emphasizes developing conferences and programs that integrate the components of the mission into public life. The Center serves as a catalyst for creative programming by first identifying issues then bringing people together. By venturing across disciplines and professional boundaries, the Conference Center transforms ideas into innovative conferences and meetings by providing expertise in three general categories.
<P>
<h3>Planning Services</h3>
The comprehensive planning services provided by the Conference Center are tailored to meet the individual needs of a program, to determine the goals and objectives, and to offer consultation services which include:
<UL>
<LI>Guidance in forming planning committees, conference organization and preparing a  conference budget
<LI>Assistance in establishing purpose and goals of  a conference
<LI>Suggestions on conference format, planning, promotion and site selection
</UL>
<h3>Support Services</h3>
The Conference Center initiates professional assistance in the following areas:
<UL>
<LI>Scheduling and arranging for meeting sites
<LI>	Providing pre- and on-site registration assistance
<LI>Coordinating hotel and travel arrangements for participants and speakers
<LI>Contracting resource people
<LI>Preparing materials for distribution before and during conference
</UL>
<h3>Administrative Services</h3>
As a natural spin-off of a growing program, the administrative management of the Conference Center includes:
<UL>
<LI>Developing and administering a financial plan for each conference budget
<LI>Identifying sources of income
<LI>Providing accountability for expenditures to sponsors and vendors
<LI>Evaluating pre-established conference goals and objectives
</UL>
<P>
<P>
<A HREF = MAILTO:"yyy@hawaii.edu">E-Mail Address: yyy@hawaii.edu </A>
<P>
<font size = 2>
<EM>NOTE: The University of Hawai`i at Manoa is an equal opportunity/affirmative
action institution and is committed to a policy of nondiscrimination on the
basis of race, sex, age, religion, color, national origin, ancestry,
disability, marital status, arrest and court record, sexual orientation, and
veteran status.  This policy covers admission and access to, and
participation, treatment and employment in the University's programs,
activities, and services.</EM>
</P>

[rev. 9-1-95]

</Body>
