<th>Molokai 8</th>			<th>Lanai 8</th>				<th>Kauai 12</th>
</tr>

</table>
<P>
A Voice for Music Learning is hosted by Aaron Mahi, Band Master of the Royal
Hawaiian Band with student guest panelists who have received awards for their
outstanding accomplishments.  During the live broadcast, telephone hook-ups
permit any cable subscriber to interact directly with the originating studio via
toll-free 800 lines.  A Voice for Music Learning is a collaborative project
combining the resources of the Hawai`i Association of Music Societies, the
Department of Education Distance Learning Program, and the University of Hawai`i
at Manoa.  The series presents an overview of the fields of musical education in
Hawai`i, and is intended to motivate parents, teachers, and decision makers to
get involved with youth music learning.
<P>
</a>
<IMG SRC ="Images/RedFade.GIF"><br>
<A NAME="MARCH">
<IMG SRC ="Images/March.GIF"> 
<P>
<strong>Shostakovich String Quartet</strong><br>
Saturday, March 2; 8:00 p.m.<br>
University of Hawai`i at Manoa Orvis Auditorium<br>
Tickets: $18 (general) and $13 (student)<br>
On sale February 8 at Harry's Music Store and Campus Center Ticket Desk<br>
or call 956-8242<br>
<P>
The highly acclaimed <strong>Shostakovich String Quartet</strong> returns to
Honolulu for the third time.  The rich repertoire of the ensemble includes over
150 pieces, with the complete cycle of all 15 Shostakovich quartets as the
crowning glory.  On this trip to Hawai`i the quartet will play Glinka, Quartet
No. 2; Shostakovich, Quartet No. 11; and Beethoven, Quartet in E-flat Major,
Op.74.  Co-sponsored by the Honolulu Chmaber Music Series.
<P>
<center>
<IMG SRC ="Images/RedLine.GIF"><br>
</center>
<P>
<strong>The Kageboushi Theatrical Company of Japan - First U.S. Tour</strong><br>
"Taketori Monogatari: The Tale of Princess Kaguya"<br>
Saturday, March 16; 2:00 p.m. & 7:30 p.m.<br>
Sunday, March 17; 2:00 p.m. & 4:30 p.m.<br>
Leeward Community College Theatre, Pearl City<br>
Tickets: $15 (general) and $10 (students and senior citizens)<br>
On sale at Leeward Community College Theatre Box Office<br>
or call 455-0385<br>
<P>
<center>
<img src = "images/Kageboushi.GIF"> 
</center>
<P>
The stunning Kageboushi Theatrical Company visits Hawaii on its first U. S.
tour.  The company's introduction of the latest technology and innovative ideas
have made it a leader in Japanese youth theater, attracting audiences of 500,000
people each year.  "Taketori Monogatari" is a classic Japanese tale more than
1,000 years old.  It tells the story of the beautiful Princess Kaguya.  The
production has appeal for children and adults alike.  Presented in cooperation
with Leeward Community College.
<P>
</a>
<IMG SRC ="Images/RedFadeReverse.GIF">
<A NAME="APRIL">
<IMG SRC ="Images/April.GIF">
<P>
<strong>Lin Shicheng and Gao Hong: An Evening of Pipa Music</strong><br>
Saturday, April 6; 7:30 p.m.<br>
Honolulu Academy of Arts - Academy Theatre<br>
Tickets: $12 (general) and $10 (students and senior citizens)<br>
On sale March 15 at the Academy Theatre, Harry's Music Store and Campus
<br>	Center Ticket Desk<br>
or call 956-7642<br>
<P>
One of the most accomplished musicians in the world, pipa master Lin Shicheng,
is making his U.S debut.  The maestro will be accompanied on this tour by one of
his top students, pipa soloist Gao Hong.  The pair will thrill Honolulu
audiences in a stunning one night only performance.  Co-sponsored by the
Honolulu Academy of Arts.
<P>
<center>
<IMG SRC ="Images/RedLine.GIF"><br>
</center>
<P>
<strong>Angeles String Quartet</strong><br>
Saturday, April 13; 8:00 p.m.<br>
University of Hawai`i at Manoa's Orvis Auditorium<br>
Tickets: $18 (general) and $13 (student)<br>
On sale March 22 at Harry's Music Store and Campus Center Ticket Desk<br>
or call 956-8242<br>
<P>
Angeles String Quartet was inadvertently formed after a magnificent response and
immediate rapport to its one time only concert in 1988.  Since then, the quartet
has become a permanent entity and an audience favorite.  It is currently engaged
in the task of recording all of Haydn's 68 string quartets.  Angeles will
perform Haydn, Op. 71, No. 3; Miklos Rozsa, Quartet No. 2, Op. 38 (1891);
Webern, Six Bagatelles; and Dvorak, "American" (Op. 96).   Co-sponsored by the
Honolulu Chamber Music Series.
<P>
<center>
<IMG SRC ="Images/RedLine.GIF"><br>
</center>

<P>
<strong>A Voice for Music Learning: Why is Music Learning Essential?</strong><br>
Monday, April 22; 7:00 p.m.<br>
Broadcast over these local cable channels:<br>
<P>
<table border=3 cellpadding=8 width="100%">
<tr>
	<th>Oahu 24</th>           
    <th>Hawai`i Kai 3</th>         
	<th>Hilo 2</th>
</tr>
