</A>
<A NAME = "NONCREDITREGINFO">
<hr>
<H3>NONCREDIT PROGRAM</H3>
<font size = 2>
<em>(all dates subject to change)</em><p>
<font size = 3>



<P>
		
Noncredit courses, offered in three terms throughout the year, are open to anyone who is at least 18 years of age or a high school graduate. Although there are no formal prerequisites for admission into the noncredit program, a specific course may require that the student have some prior experience in order to obtain maximum benefit. Noncredit courses do not apply toward the requirements of a college degree.<br>
Many of the noncredit courses listed in the TABLOID qualify for professional continuing education units. If requested of the instructor at the first class meeting, CCECS can issue certificates of completion denoting the number of contact hours (INSTRUCTIONAL HOURS) in the course to those students whose instructors verify in writing that they attended at least 80% of the classes upon completion of the course. These certificates can be submitted by students to their respective professional organizations for review and granting of continuing education credits.<p>
<strong>ABOUT YOUR ENROLLMENT</strong><br>
To ensure that your enrollment is processed quickly and accurately, please provide all information requested on the registration form and remit with full payment. You may assume enrollment is accepted and report to class at the time and place listed unless otherwise notified. Registrations received prior to JANUARY 6, 1997 will be held until that date and will be processed in random order along with in-person registrations. If enrolling less than five working days prior to the start of class, you should call 956-8400 to confirm enrollment and/or if the class will be held as announced.<p>
<Strong>DISABILITY ACCESS</strong><br>
Persons with disabilities who may require access services should contact the Office of Student Affairs (956-8400) at the time of registration.<p>
<strong>HOW TO ENROLL</strong><br>
Register Early! You are encouraged to register early because enrollment is limited in most courses. Early registration also helps to insure sufficient enrollment since courses may be canceled if the minimum enrollment requirements are not met.<br>
<strong>Method of Payment. </strong>Full payment must accompany your registration. You may pay by cash; personal check, money order, or cashier's check payable to the University of Hawaii; MasterCard or VISA; or business purchase order.<br>
<Strong>Register by Mail.</strong> Use the registration form on this page. If more space is needed, feel free to duplicate as many copies as needed. Mail completed form with payment to:<br>
UHM-College of Continuing Education<br>
and Community Service<Br>
2530 Dole Street, Sakamaki C104<Br>
Honolulu, HI  96822<br>
<Strong>Register by Fax. </strong>You may fax your registration to 956-3752 (24 hrs. unattended) beginning January 6, 1997. All fax registrations must include VISA or MasterCard number, expiration date and card holder's signature. Please print and sign legibly and use a clean registration form to insure that your information can be read. If you do not receive a confirmation receipt within 7 working days, please call 956-8400 to verify your enrollment. <br>
<Strong>Register in Person. </strong>At CCECS Office of Student Affairs; 2530 Dole Street, Sakamaki Hall, room C104; Mon-Thurs 8:00 am-7:45 pm; Fri 8:00 am-4:15 pm.<br>
<strong>Register by Phone. </strong>You may register by phone beginning January 6, 1997. Please have the course information and your credit card information when you call. Call 956-8581 Mon-Thur from 8 am-7:45 pm; Fri 8:00 am-4:15 pm. <br>
<Strong>Deadline. </strong>Students should enroll at least five (5) working days prior to the start of a course and may assume enrollment is accepted unless otherwise notified. Students registering after this deadline should contact the Office of Student Affairs (956-8400) to verify enrollment and status of the course.<Br>
<Strong>Returned Checks. </strong>Checks returned by the maker's bank for any reason will result in a $15.00 charge. In addition, interest on the $15.00 returned check charge will be assessed at a rate of $.10 a month, for the period beginning the first calendar day after the date of notification from the bank that the check is dishonored, to the date paid.<br>
<strong>Withdrawals/Refunds. </strong>Request to withdraw from classes must be made in person or in writing (postmarked), to CCECS, by the specified deadlines as follows. For courses six weeks or longer, full refunds are permitted if request is made on or before the fifth working day (including first class session) after the class begins. For short courses or seminars, one to five weeks in length, full refunds are permitted up to the last working day before the course begins. No refunds are permitted thereafter. Please allow approximately four to six weeks for refund processing. NOTE: Failure to attend class or notification of withdrawal to the instructor does not constitute withdrawal. Students registering by purchase order will be billed regardless of non-attendance unless notification of withdrawal is made to CCECS by the specified refund deadlines.<p>
<Strong>Holidays. </strong>Classes are not held on state or federal holidays, unless otherwise stated.<p>
SPRING TERM HOLIDAYS<p>
<li>JAN 20:  MARTIN LUTHER KING JUNIOR DAY<Br>
<li>FEB 17:  PRESIDENTS DAY<Br>
<li>MAR 26:  KUHIO DAY<Br>
<li>MAR 28:  GOOD FRIDAY<p>
<strong>PARKING. </strong><br>Parking is permitted on campus after 4 pm during weekday evenings and all day on Saturday and Sunday for $3 (payable upon entering campus). Please be aware that there is a $20 change limit at the entrances to campus lots; exact change is appreciated. Monthly evening parking tags may be purchased for $16 per month at the Traffic Office, 1980 East-West Road, Monday through Friday, from 8:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. Students must present their blue registration receipt at the time of purchase. If your course is canceled, a full refund may be obtained at the Traffic Office; bring your tag and your receipt. For additional information on purchasing evening parking tags, please call the Traffic Office at 956-8899.<p>

<P>
<P>
<a name = "TEXTBOOKINFO">
<center><h3>TEXTBOOK INFORMATION</h3></center>
<P>

<Strong>TEXTBOOK PURCHASES</strong><br>
If you must purchase a textbook for your class, the "plus textbook" notation is included in the course information. Books for Continuing Education (CCECS) classes are stocked in a special CCECS NONCREDIT section at the University Bookstore. The only information you need to find your book is the course number and title since books are shelved according to this information. If your textbook is included in the course fee, this is noted in the course information and books are normally distributed at the first class session. Optional textbooks are not required but are available at the Bookstore for interested students. The Bookstore is located in the Campus Center Building. Hours (subject to change):<br>
UHM BOOKSTORE:<br>
Monday-Friday     8:15 am4:45 pm<br>
Saturday               8: 15 am11:45 am<p>
Any information contained in this Tabloid, including statement of fees, course offerings, schedules, etc., is subject to change without notice or obligation. The University of Hawaii at Manoa and the College of Continuing Education and Community Service are not responsible for any cancellation/change charges assessed by airlines or travel agencies.


For more information on the Bookstore, <a href =
"gopher://gopher.hawaii.edu/11/Services/Bookstore">clickhere</a>.<br>
<P>
Students Should Insure That Their Tuberculosis And Immunization Needs Are Current.
<P>

</A>

<A NAME = "REFUNDINFO">
<center>

<h3>REFUNDS</h3>
</center>
<P>

For courses six weeks or longer, full refunds are permitted if request is made
on or before the fifth working day (including the first class session) after the
class begins.  For short courses or seminars, one to five weeks in length, full
refunds are permitted up to the last working day before the course begins. 
Refund requests must be made in person or in writing (postmarked) by the above
specified deadlines.  No refunds are permitted thereafter.  Refunds for check
and cash payments will be mailed and refunds for charge payments will be
credited to your account.  Please allow approximately three to five weeks for
refund processing.<P>

<strong>NOTE</strong>:  Failure to attend class or notification of withdrawal to
the instructor does not constitute withdrawal.  Students registering by purchase
order will be billed regardless of non-attendance unless notification of
withdrawal is made to the College by the specified refund deadlines.<P>

Refund requests may be mailed to:<P>
<address>
UHM-College of Continuing Education & Community Service<br>
Office of Student Affairs<br>
2530 Dole Street, Sakamaki C104<br>
Honolulu, Hawaii 96822<br>
</address>
<P>
</A>
<P>
