<h3> PARKING AT the University of Hawai`i at Manoa </h3>
<P>
<strong>Parking ($3 upon entry) may be found:</strong>
<P>
On Campus: Students are permitted to park on campus in any zone after 4 pm during weekday evenings and all day on Saturday and Sunday.  (Please avoid parking in specially marked stalls.)  To enter upper campus from University Avenue, turn onto Maile Way.  To enter upper campus from Dole Street, turn onto East-West Road.  
Peripheral lots near Sinclair Library and the Architecture building are accessed from University Avenue (traveling mauka).  Peripheral lots near the Music Building and near the Law School are accessed from Dole street (traveling Diamond Head.)  
Please be sure to pay parking fee and display tag before parking in peripheral lots.<P>

Parking Structure/Lower Campus: From Dole Street, turn right on Lower Campus road (first stoplight after the intersection of University and Dole.) 
<P>


<strong>Evening Parking Passes</strong>
<P>
Monthly evening parking tags may be purchased for $16 per month at the Traffic Office, 1980 East-West Road, Monday through Friday from 8 am-4 pm.  Students must present their blue registration receipt at the time of purchase.  <P>

NOTE:  CCECS has made special arrangements to sell evening parking tags at Sakamaki C104 on the following days and times:  January 6, January 27, February 13, and March 14 from 4:30-8 pm; and February 8 from 9 am to 12 pm.
<P>
<h3>
Directions to the University of Hawai`i at Manoa</h3>
<P>
<strong>From Honolulu International Airport:</strong>
<P>
Join H-1 (Lunalilo Freeway) EASTBOUND from Airport <br>
Continue on H-1 approx. 7 miles <br>
Take Exit 24B - University Avenue <br>
Go NORTH on University Avenue 1 block to the Dole Street intersection and the entrance to the campus. 
<P>
<strong>From Waikiki (e.g., hotels on Kalakaua Ave. or Kuhio Ave.):</strong>
<P>
Go NORTH on a side street and turn LEFT (WEST) onto Ala Wai Blvd. <br>
Continue WEST and turn RIGHT (NORTH) onto McCully St. <br>
Cross over the Ala Wai Canal, then turn RIGHT (EAST) onto Kapiolani Blvd.  Travel approx. 0.4 miles then turn <br>
LEFT (NORTH) onto University Ave.  Travel along University Ave. approx. 0.7 miles to the Dole Street intersection <br>
and entrance to the campus. 
<P>
<strong>From Eastern Oahu:</strong>
<P>
Join H-1 WESTBOUND <br>
Take Exit 24B - University Ave. <br>
Go NORTH on University Ave. 1 block to the Dole Street intersection and the entrance to the campus. <br>
<P>
<h3>Off-Campus Locations</h3>
<P>

* Ala Wai Golf Course Clubhouse, 404 Kapahulu Avenue
<br>* Bishop Museum Planetarium, 1525 Bernice Street
<br>* Camp Timberline, Waianae
<br>* CHART Rehabilitation of Hawaii, Inc. (Honolulu), 1505 Dillingham Boulevard, Suite 110
<br>* CHART Rehabilitation of Hawaii, Inc. (Waipahu), 94-810 Moloalo Street, 2nd Floor
<br>* Computer Training Company, Inc., Suite 1185, Pacific Tower, 1001 Bishop Street
<br>* Hawaii Kai Golf Course, 8902 Kalanianaole Hwy
<br>* JMD Educational Center, 99-1269 Iwaena Street (see directions below)
<br>* Kaiser Hospital (Moanalua), Conference Room C and D, 2nd Floor, 3288 Moanalua Road
<br>* Kalama Beach Park (Boetcher Estate), 248 North Kalaheo Avenue
<br>* Kalani High School, 4680 Kalanianaole Highway
<br>* Keely Luke Photographie Studio, 627 South Street
<br>* Newtown Golf Range, 98-330 Kaahele Street
<br>* Oda Ballet School, 36-D Bates Street
<br>* Olomana Golf Links, 41-1801 Kalanianaole Highway
<br>* Paki Hale, 3840 Paki Avenue
<br>* Salt Lake District Park, 1159 Ala Lilikoi Place
<br>* Sea Life Park Marine Education Foundation Classroom, Makapuu Point, 41-202 Kalanianaole Hwy
<br>* TEMARI Center for Asian and Pacific Arts, 1329A 10th Avenue
<br>* Tokai University, 2241 Kapiolani Boulevard
<br>* Travel University International (Ala Moana Bldg), 1441 Kapiolani Boulevard
<br>* West Loch Golf Course, 91-1126 Okupe Street<p>

<strong> JMD Educational Center:</strong><P>

JMD Educational Center<br>
 99-1269 Iwaena St. <br>
(808) 486-5638 Reservations <br>
(808)734-5053 Information<P>

From Honolulu: Follow H-1 and continue on Moanalua Raod. Take the Stadium
Off-Ramp, make a right at the stoplight at the bottom of ramp, turn left at
Iwaiwa St. next right at Iwaena St.<P>
From the Airport: Get on Nimitz Hwy. Going towards Waikiki, take a left at
Puuloa Rd. Follow until you get to the Aiea On-Ramp, Follow H-1, take the
Stadium Off-Ramp and follow the above directions.<P>
From Pearl City: Follow H-1 and take the Halawa Heights exit, follow the Halawa
Heights signs and turn right at Halawa Valley cut-off, turn left onto Iwaiwa St.
and right at Iwaena St.
<P>
