<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Extended Programs</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor ="#000000" text = "#ffffff" link = "#ccff00" vlink =
"#cc00ff">
<CENTER>
<img src = "images/EPHeader.GIF">
</CENTER>
<FONT SIZE = 3>
<P>
<HR SIZE = 3>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE = 3>
Under Construction... please pardon any inconvenience.<P>
<STRONG>The Extended, or Credit Program</STRONG> establishes and
administers credit 
course programs designed to serve individuals who are unable to
attend the regular University day program. The program 
provides these individuals an opportunity to earn a college 
degree, upgrade their professional occupational skills or 
achieve personal enrichment. Courses are offered on the 
Manoa campus, at various public and private schools as well 
as other locations.
<P>

<img src = "images/Evening.GIF"><br>
<img src = "images/YellowSwach.GIF"><P>

The On-Campus Evening Credit Program offers general education 
courses required of all degree curricula. The courses are programmed 
into four ten-week terms per year. In addition, courses sufficient for

students to complete all requirements for a bachelor's degree in 
Psychology and Liberal Studies are offered.
<P>
<a href = "http://www-ccecs.arthum.hawaii.edu/Accel/Accel.HTML">Click Here for the Summer 1996 Accel...</a><p>
<a href = "http://www-ccecs.arthum.hawaii.edu/FALL_ACCEL/Accel.HTML">Click Here for the Fall 1996 Accel...</a><p>
<P>
<img src = "images/Teachers.GIF"><br>
<img src = "images/YellowSwach.GIF"><P>


The courses offered through the Teachers Program enable State 
teachers to enhance their professional career and to meet requirements

of the State Department of Education. The State Teachers Program:
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Provides for the educational needs of teachers in the public 
and private schools;</li>
<LI>Administers the Alternative Basic Certification in Special 
Education Program (ABCSE).</li><p>
<blockquote>
This is an integrated, on-the-job special education teacher 
training program. The ABCSE Program which was implemented 
in Fall 1991, is designed for personnel who wish to work with 
children and youth, at the preschool, elementary and/or 
secondary levels, who are identified as having 
disabilities at all levels of severity.<BR>
The ABCSE Program does not lead to a University of Hawai'i 
diploma or degree. Rather, it is a non-degree program 
that consists of a 24 credit sequence of course work, the 
successful completion of which results in an institutional 
recommendation to the Hawai'i Department of 
Education for a Basic Special Education teaching 
certificate. The ABCSE Program is offered to eligible 
participants, who are not trained in education, but, who 
wish to become certified special educators.
</blockquote>
</UL>
<P>
<a href = "http://www-ccecs.arthum.hawaii.edu/DOE/DOE.HTML">Click Here for 1996 DOE Summer Courses...</a>
<P>

<img src = "images/CRSP.GIF"><br>
<img src = "images/YellowSwach.GIF"><P>

The Credit Special Programs provide courses which 
are tailored to meet unique needs of a target group. The 
programs may compress the work into shorter time periods, 
adapt to special locations, more convenient hours, etc., in 
response to special needs. In addition, advanced and 
in-service courses are offered to teachers in Hawai'i and the 
Pacific Basin.
<OL>
<LI>Certificate In Public Administration Program</li>
<LI>Nursing Program</li>
<LI>Overseas </li>
<LI>Master's Degree In Social Work</li>
<LI>School of Public Health Courses</li>
<LI>Dual Enrollment</li>
<LI>School of Library & Information Studies Courses</li>
<LI>Educational Administration Courses</li>
<LI>Medical Technology Courses</li>
<LI>Imi Ho'ola Program</li>
<LI>University Affiliated Program</li>
</OL>
<P>

<img src = "images/Maui.GIF"><br>
<img src = "images/YellowSwach.GIF"><P>

The objective of the <A
HREF="http://www.maui.com/~starfire/outreach/web.html">Maui Outreach 
Program </a> is to offer undergraduate and
graduate educational opportunities to students on Maui, Moloka'i and
Lana'i. The
program offers a 
Bachelor of Arts Degree in Liberal Studies, with the major equivalent
in 
Human Relations in Organizations. This program is available only to
students 
on Maui and includes HITS courses in addition to on-site courses.
<P>
A Bachelor in Elementary Education is offered to students on Maui,
Moloka'i, 
Lana'i and in Hana. The Maui Community College Skybridge System is 
utilized in order to reach students on Moloka'i, Lana'i and in Hana. 
Some students in this program already have an undergraduate degree 
and are working on a Basic Teacher Certification in Elementary 
Education. Courses are also offered to Department of Education 
teachers who wish to obtain the Professional Diploma or who are
working 
on DOE reclassification.
<P>
<img src = "images/Kauai.GIF"><br>
<img src = "images/YellowSwach.GIF"><P>

The Kaua'i Outreach Program offers a series of courses to enable 
students for initial Basic Certification by the State of 
Hawai'i as elementary school teachers and credits towards the 
Bachelor of Elementary Education Program. Additionally, the 
program offers courses toward a Master of Education in 
Instructional Leadership and School Leadership.
<P>
<img src = "images/Legislative.GIF"><br>
<img src = "images/YellowSwach.GIF"><P>

The Legislative Intern Program provides full-time juniors and seniors 
attending UHM with an opportunity to learn about the functions of the 
Hawai'i State Legislature, including the process by which bills are 
introduced and passed, how the committee system functions and the 
relationship between the State House of Representatives and 
State Senate.
<P>
<img src = "images/Executive.GIF"><br>
<img src = "images/YellowSwach.GIF"><P>

The Executive Intern Program provides full-time juniors and seniors 
attending UHM with an opportunity to learn about the functions of the 
Executive Branch of the State Government and to provide an office or 
agency with additional qualified personnel to aid the agency in
fulfilling 
its objectives by performing meaningful tasks.
<P>
<P>
<A HREF = MAILTO:"okinaga@hawaii.edu">E-Mail Address:
okinaga@hawaii.edu </A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE = 2>
<EM>NOTE: The University of Hawai'i at Manoa is an equal
opportunity/affirmative
action institution and is committed to a policy of nondiscrimination
on the
basis of race, sex, age, religion, color, national origin, ancestry,
disability, marital status, arrest and court record, sexual
orientation, and
veteran status.  This policy covers admission and access to, and
participation, treatment and employment in the University's programs,
activities, and services.</EM>
</P>

[rev. 9-1-95]

</Body>
