<IMG SRC = "Images/Cover.GIF"><p>
<center>
March 14, 1996</center><P>

Memo to:	All Department Certificated Personnel<P>

From:		Donald R. Nugent, Ed.D., Assistant <br>
			Superintendent Office of Personnel Services<P>

Subject:	1996 Summer College Courses<P>

The Department, in collaboration with the College of Continuing
Education and Community Service (CCECS), University of Hawai'i at
Manoa, announces the 1996 slate of summer courses selected, arranged,
or funded by the Department of Education for its certified personnel. 
The announcement is being sent to all schools in the Department as a
convenience to those who plan to enroll in summer courses. 
Participation is voluntary.<P>

The courses in the announcement are listed by program areas. 
Registration is required for all courses and will have to be through
the CCECS, University of Hawai'i at Manoa, except for those courses
offered through the Continuing Education and Community Service,
University of Hawaii at HILO.
Should there be any questions about the Department of Education funded
summer courses, please contact the appropriate DOE course sponsor
named in the announcement.<P>


<P>


Call the appropriate DOE Course Sponsor if you have any questions
regarding the DOE-Funded courses in this tabloid.<P>

Call the UH-CCECS's Office of Student Affairs at 956-8400 for
registration information regarding the Non-Funded courses in this
tabloid.<P>

</BODY>

