<TITLE>
Document Tracking System Tutorial
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor = "cfffff">
Under Construction!<P>
<CENTER><H1>CCECS Document Tracking System (DTS)</H1></CENTER>
<HR SIZE = 4>
<FONT SIZE = 5>

<UL>
<LI> How and What is the DTS? (And what it isn't) </LI>
<LI> Future Implementations </LI>
<LI> Logging into the System </LI>
<LI> The HOME Card </LI>
<LI> Document Window</LI>
<LI> Preferences Window</LI>
<LI> Administer Window</LI>
<LI> Quick Process</LI>
<LI> Comments </LI>
</UL>

<HR SIZE = 4>
<FONT SIZE = 3>

<H2> How and What is the DTS? (And what it isn't) </H2>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
The DTS (Document Tracking System) was implemented on June to September of 
1995 after a discussion with, then the Interim Dean of the College of Continuing
Education, Gerald Morihara.  He wanted a system that would stream-line the processing
of various documents that flowed throughout the College.  The DTS was a tool to
"coerce" staff members to process the documents that entered into their in-tray in
a timely manner.  The system was to clue the originator of a document to the different stages 
of processing his/her document was expected to go through and take the appropriate steps
if deviations occured.
<P>
The DTS logs the flow of a real document as it changes hands within the College.  It is not
a substitute for actual forms.  Forms are not represented electronically by the system --
the system is not a forms editor.  Instead, it holds information about the form/document(s) and who
may currently have it.
<P>
The DTS was implemented using ACI`US 4th Dimension (4D) relational database.  The server is a currently
a Macintosh IIfx with 32 Megabytes of RAM and can support 25 simultaneous users.  CCECS is networked 
via 10BaseT supporting a total of 72 nodes.  Client machines vary from IIcx's to PowerMac 7100's.

<H2> Logging into the DTS</H2>
<img align = right border = 1 src ="Images/ClientIcon.GIF">
The 4D Client software should be installed and on your desktop.  Double click on the 
4D Client Icon (as shown on the right) to connect to the 4D Server.
<P>
A "Connect to data server" window should appear in a few seconds:
<P>
<img border = 1 src= "Images/SelectDTS.GIF"> <p>
Make sure "art" is selected under the <em>Zones</em> window and "DTS 0.93.src.comp" is selected in the
<em>Data Servers</em> window and click on the OK button.<P>
The <em> Password </em> window should appear:<P>
<img border = 1 src= "Images/Login.GIF"><p>
Type in your user name and password (usually none) and click on the "Connect" button".  Wait a few 
seconds until you see the DTS Home Card.<P>

<HR>
<h2> The Home Card</h2>
<P>
The Home Card represents the entry point to all the functions offered by the DTS.  The following
functions are available:<p>

<img border = 1 src= "Images/Home.GIF"><p>


